Heat until hot, then layer on top of rice.
Spread nacho cheese soup on top.
Swirl soup into mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts into mixture. Serve with nacho chips.

title: cherry date skillet cookies
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar and dates.
Remove from heat.
Add egg and return to heat.
Continue to cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, except 2 1/2 cups coconut. Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Shape into balls and roll in 2 1/2 cups of coconut.

title: pecan pie with a twist(a twist of lemon)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine eggs, corn syrup, vanilla extract, and lemon juice. Mix with a fork until blended. Combine sugar, brown sugar, and flour. Mix well and then add to egg mixture. Stir in butter. Put pecans in pie crust and then pour the filling over the pecans. Bake for 1 hour. Cool before slicing.

title: grandma's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 14.

title: bread and butter pickles number 1
directions: Slice vegetables thin.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice and let stand 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil and pack in hot, sterilized jars; seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: rainbow crayons
directions: Put a foil baking cup in each cup of a muffin tin.
Chop the old peeled crayons into 1/4-inch pieces and place them in the baking cups.
Heat the crayons at 400° for 5 minutes or until the crayon pieces just begin to melt.
Remove them before the colors mix together and become muddy.
When the crayons have cooled, peel off the baking cups.
Crayons may also be melted outside in the sun on a hot day.

title: pumpkin roll(alice miser's)
directions: Beat eggs on high. Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet and top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican brunch
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat well at medium with electric beaters.
Stir remaining ingredients and pour into a well-greased 9-inch quiche pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° and bake about 20 minutes or until set. Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 6.

title: berry and pineapple crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Combine cake mix, butter, 1/4 cup sugar, oats and cinnamon in large bowl.
Rub together in fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal and holds together in large moist clumps.
Mix in pecans.
Mix frozen
blueberries, pineapple with syrup and remaining 1/2 cup sugar in prepared dish.
Cover fruit with cake mix topping.
Bake crumble until fruit is bubbling thickly and topping is brown and crisp, about 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: disappearing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook shells in boiling water with salt.
Drain, rinse in cold water, drain and set aside.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Mix together brown sugar, flour and butter in 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread on first mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir in rice, onion flakes, salt, soup and water.
Place chicken breasts over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: home-canned bread and butter pickles(consider doubling recipe.)
directions: Wash cukes and slice into thin-medium thick rounds. Chop onions and peppers. Combine with cukes and salt. Let stand 3 hours then drain.

title: crispy buttermilk oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with foil.
Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray.
In shallow dish, combine flour and lemon-pepper seasoning; mix well.
Place buttermilk in another shallow dish.
In third shallow dish, combine corn flake crumbs and cornmeal; mix well.
To bread chicken, dip chicken in flour mixture to coat.
Dip in buttermilk; dip in crumb mixture to coat.
Place chicken in foil-lined pan. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make ground beef and egg into 18 balls.
Brown in oil.
Drain off oil.
Add pineapple juice.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook until it begins to thicken, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs and chunky pineapple.
Cut green peppers into thin slices lengthwise and put on top.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Melt cheese in a sauce pan over very low heat. Add cream and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Remove from heat. Add shrimp, mayo, and grated onion. Spread on toasted bread and cut in squares, rectangles, or diamonds. Can be packaged in freezer cartons. Freeze at once. Broil until lightly browned.

title: cheese fingers
directions: Cut cheese into strips.
Roll strips in flour.
Beat an egg; dip strips in egg mixture.
Roll in untoasted bread crumbs.
Be sure to coat cheese real good.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Deep fat fry until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: grandmother busick's breakfast muffins
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: buttermilk-blue cheese dressing
directions: In blender container, combine buttermilk and mayonnaise. Process until thoroughly combined. Stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer to a bowl or jar that has a tight fitting cover. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Just before serving, stir well. Makes 12 servings.

title: herbed tomato-cheese bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix and milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead 3 or 4 times.
Press into bottom and up sides of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with tomato slices.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Spoon mixture over tomatoes; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Yields about 12 servings.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine beans, ketchup, molasses, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: egg and sausage delight
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes. Brown sausage and drain. Mix with cheese and bread. Blend other ingredients in blender. Pour over sausage mixture and stir.
Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Cover with Saran Wrap. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour. Serves 12.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in 2-quart baking dish.
Tear or cube stale bread.
Sprinkle evenly in dish.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and sugar; mix well.
Add raisins, vanilla, salt and spices.
Pour over bread.
Dot with 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, plain or with whipped topping or lemon sauce.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter, sugar and syrup.
Mix well. Roll in 3/4 inch balls and coat with dipping chocolate made by melting the chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Coat the balls by inserting a toothpick into them and lowering them into the chocolate.
Makes about 40.

title: mystery salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium sized bowl.
Sprinkle 2 or 3 more walnut halves, chopped, on top.
Refrigerate, covered. Serves 10 to 12.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Let set 10 minutes while you make icing.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix well the cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Stir and dissolve the vinegar and sugar.
Pour over pickles.
Pack in containers and freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat
eggs,
add
other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together; dough will be sticky, but in a ball. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 11 minutes. Rotate sheets halfway through baking time. Careful not to burn bottoms. Cookies will harden as they cool.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: three-cheese macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine hot macaroni, soup, milk, seasonings, 1/4 cup each of the cheeses and 1/2 of the onions.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheeses and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer or until onions are golden brown.

title: mom's spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
In large bowl, mix butter, Parmesan, salt, pepper and egg.
Add spaghetti and toss to coat well.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown ground chuck in large saucepan, adding onion, pepper and garlic just as meat starts to cook.
When meat is browned, drain off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar and oregano.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Can be divided into 2 meals and frozen.

title: apple rolls
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil in saucepan.
Continue to boil until the mixture has reduced to half.
Peel and core the apples.
Grate the apples.
Make a biscuit dough and roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with softened oleo.
Sprinkle with sugar. Spread grated apples on dough; sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Roll up like a cinnamon roll. Slice 1-inch slices and place in a greased baking dish.
Pour syrup mixture over the rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: savory steak rub
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in a covered container. Rub over steaks before grilling or broiling.
Will season four to five steaks.
Yield:
1/4 cup.

title: family orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.	Add mayonnaise and beat well with mixer.
Then add the remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
I usually double the recipe - it lasts for days. Great to make early.

title: beer-b-cue sauce(makes 1 quart)
directions: Bring to boil.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Add 1 medium onion, thinly sliced and 1/2 lemon, thinly sliced.

title: low-fat pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
In a medium-size bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cloves and cinnamon.
In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites, pumpkin and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour mixture; mix well. Fold in dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies; 1 gram of fat per cookie.

title: comforting cookies
directions: Preheat 350.
In large mixing bowl combine oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add sugars and mix well.
In separate bowl combine flour, soda, and salt.
Add to sugar mixture beating until blended, Stir in corn flakes, quick oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by Tbsp. 3 inches apart in lightly greased cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 9 Dozen.

title: red velvet cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and food color; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Stir baking soda into vinegar.
Fold gently into batter (do not beat).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Frost with Sour Cream-Pecan Frosting.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add applesauce.
Blend flour, soda, salt and spices, then blend in raisins, nuts and gumdrops.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Mix together and keep in jar.
Use spoonful in cup of water. Makes a nice gift.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in large saucepan.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take beaten eggs; add a little amount of hot milk mixture to them.
Then add egg mixture to milk mixture.
Heat 1 minute longer.
Chill for 2 hours.
Then add heavy cream and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into ice cream maker and turn on.
Use ice, rock salt and water as directed.

title: ruby red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until berries are thawed and separated.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Carefully spread with sour cream; chill.
Dissolve cherry jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add pineapple and cranberry sauce; mix well.
Allow to thicken slightly.
Carefully spoon over sour cream mixture; chill.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
If desired, top each with a dollop of mayonnaise and garnish with a mint leaf.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: manicotti with cheese
directions: Cook manicotti (or shells) and drain.
Cool in a single layer. Combine cheeses, parsley, salt and pepper for filling; spoon into manicotti.
Spread a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange manicotti in single layer on sauce.
(If the large shells are used, put the open side down.) Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato	sauce.	Mix the cottage
cheese
and sour cream, and in
a	greased
casserole alternate layers of hamburger, noodles
and sour cream-cottage cheese mixture.
Bake at 225° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add and mix all ingredients, then add extra for own personal taste.
(All ingredients except molasses can be mixed with salt-free brands, for those who are heart conscience.)

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in boiler. Add peanuts and noodles. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet. Let cool.

title: honey carrots
directions: Wash and trim carrots.
Cook in boiling water until tender and drain.
Melt margarine in skillet; add sugar, honey and carrots. Cook over low heat, turning often until well glazed.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley or mint and serve.

title: honey spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large container.
Blend ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning ribs occasionally.
Set oven at 300°.
Arrange ribs on rack and bake 2 hours.
Baste occasionally and turn once during cooking time. Makes 6 servings.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat into ungreased oblong pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Arrange apple slices on crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Drizzle over apples.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are lightly brown. Can be served warm with ice cream.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix everything, except popcorn, in large saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda, quickly stirring it in.
Pour over popcorn.
(I use a large stainless steel bowl.)
Stir gently until popcorn is well coated. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir caramel corn every 15 minutes during the hour.
Stir it gently a couple times after baking to keep it from clumping together.

title: washington "pie"
directions: Beat eggs until very light and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in butter, melted in milk.
Sift flour with baking powder and beat into egg-milk mixture very quickly. Pour into 2 buttered 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out onto rack and finish cooling.
Put layers together with jelly.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: "sweet 'n low" brownies
directions: Combine margarine and cocoa.
Combine flour, nuts, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, add Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Beat in cocoa mixture.
Fold in flour.
Spray 8-inch baking pan.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt chips in a bowl in the microwave for about 3-4 minutes stirring once in the middle.
Add peanuts and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Place casserole in a pan of hot water and bake for 1 hour, until firm and golden. (Can serve with baked ham or pork chops.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream puff shells
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine butter and water in saucepan and stir over moderate heat until butter is melted. Turn heat to low. Add flour all at once.
Stir vigorously for about 1 minute or until mixture forms ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat.

Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition with a wooden spoon or electric mixer on medium speed. Continue beating for 1 minute or until satiny smooth and spoonful breaks away sharply from rest of mixture.

title: stickey chicken
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly combine first 8 ingredients.
Rub mixture into chicken, inside and out, patting mixture into skin to make sure it is evenly distributed.
Place in sealable plastic bag, seal and refrigerate overnight.

title: reeses cups
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter, oleo and vanilla well with mixer and roll into balls.
Chill.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper to dry.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain.
Put soup, milk, onions, onion salt (if desired), salt, pepper, celery seed and garlic powder with potatoes.
Bring to boil.
Separate clams from clam juice.
Put juice in soup mixture.
Then add clams and let simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Put in butter.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: oriental wings(makes 24 appetizer servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each wing at joints; discard tips. Wash, drain and dry wings.
Mix together soy and hoisin sauces, rice vinegar, honey, Cajun seasoning and garlic.
Dip wings in sauce.
Arrange in single layer on foil-lined baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes; remove from oven and turn, spooning any remaining sauce over wings.
Return to oven and bake until dark brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be made ahead, refrigerated and reheated in foil at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: yippity yippity dip
directions: Cook meat, onion, green pepper, garlic and spices until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off grease.
Add catsup, tomato sauce and sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Drain off grease again (this step is important).
Add cheeses and mix well.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain liquid from salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Put salmon in bowl.
In a small bowl put egg, salmon liquid and baking powder and beat until foamy.
Add egg mixture to salmon and mix.
Add flour, seasoning and onion, mixing after each ingredient.
Shape into cakes and fry in vegetable oil or spray oil until brown. Makes 7 to 8 cakes.

title: caramel apples(club member: ashley wilson)
directions: Wash and remove stems and blossoms from apples. In top of double boiler over hot water, heat caramel, salt and water until mixture is smooth. Keeping sauce over hot water, place each apple in hot sauce. Spoon sauce over apples until apples are completely covered. Insert skewer in stem end. Remove apples from sauce and chill.

title: grandma's holiday cake
directions: Chop raisins and dates.
Pour the boiling water, in which the soda has been dissolved, over fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, then the spices and fruit, then flour.
Fold in the beaten egg white.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in loaf pan in a 350° oven.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend all ingredients together and roll dough into small balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° until lightly brown.
The cheese wafer has a nutty texture and taste.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies to look like dirt.
Set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk and blend in Cool Whip.
Set aside.

title: sweet 'n sour strips
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Drain pineapple chunks and reserve juice.
Cut green pepper into strips.
In medium skillet, heat oil. Add chicken and brown on both sides, 5 to 6 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine sweet and sour sauce mix, reserved pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Pour over chicken.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: quick jam cake
directions: Mix well. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour. Ice with favorite icing.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix flour and cocoa.
In a double boiler mix egg yolks and sugar; add flour mixture, slowly add milk.	Bring water to a boil; reduce heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.	Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: cherry raspberry sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in reserved liquids from fruits.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly; stir in fruit.
Excellent served over ice cream, pudding or pound cake. Store in refrigerator.

title: leavenworth lemon bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix, pudding mix, 1 cup water, eggs and grated rind of lemon for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: ray's ultimate summer fruit stinger
directions: Cut the top out of the cantaloupe like you would a Halloween pumpkin. Spoon out the seeds, leaving the melon hollow. Drain fruit cocktail and pour into melon. Fill remaining area in melon with vodka. Replace cut-out top on cantaloupe and place in refrigerator for a minimum of three hours (overnight is even better). Pour contents from melon into a large bowl. Cut cantaloupe in half. Scoop out cantaloupe using a small melon scoop and add to fruit. Serve and enjoy.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Beat until thick, then fold in nondairy topping.

title: chocolate butter-cream frosting
directions: In a large bowl, beat at high speed and cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Gradually beat in melted chocolate until creamy.
If too soft, refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Add salt and pepper to meat.
Cook hamburger meat until red color disappears.
Cover.
Set aside.
Mix rice according to directions on box.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Add egg one at a time, beating at least 15 minutes. Fold in pineapple and bananas. Pour in graham cracker pie crust. Top with Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: saucy cheddar veggies
directions: Stir together soup, cheese and pepper until smooth.
Stir in vegetables.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: string pie
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and pepper in a large skillet until meat is brown, stirring well. Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce and mix well.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Set aside.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken first in egg mix, then in potato flakes mixture.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in 12-inch pizza pan and seal well. Spoon cooked sausage over unbaked crust; sprinkle on hash browns and then cheese.
Beat next 5 ingredients together and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: green tomato marmalade
directions: In blender mix together green tomatoes (ground), sugar and salt.
Pour into saucepan and cook on store top on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes until transparent.
Add Jell-O, jar and seal.

title: mud hen cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given, except nuts, brown sugar and egg white.
Spread very thin in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Beat reserved egg white stiff; add the brown sugar.
Spread over nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: rice custard pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients. Stir in scalded milk. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Set dish in a pan of hot water 1-inch deep. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread in half-inch wide strips.
Arrange in layers in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with nuts. Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour over bread.
Garnish top with nuts and bake in slow oven. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: reuben appetizer squares
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix
baking mix, milk and oil until soft dough forms.
Press
into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sauerkraut and
corned
beef.
Mix mayonnaise, relish and catsup. Spread over corned beef.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly and
crust is golden brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook chopped onions in butter.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Heat and stir in sour cream and curry powder.
Add chicken. Serve over rice with golden raisins, tops of scallions, almonds and chutney.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening and stir in buttermilk.
Knead a few times; roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake in 450° oven for 12 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions into rings.
Beat the egg into the buttermilk. Dip the onion rings into the milk and egg mixture.
Cover with flour.

title: toll house pie
directions: Melt and cool butter; beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, brown sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Blend in cooled butter; fold in chips and nuts.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until berries are soft (about 10 minutes).
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water in a small bowl.
Add to blueberry mixture.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sugar over rhubarb.
Sprinkle the jello over the sugar.
Add the marshmallows.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar and Crisco. Add egg; beat well.
Add the milk, flour and baking powder. Drizzle this over top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter.
Add raisins.
Combine buttermilk, egg and baking soda.
Stir buttermilk mixture into flour mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Using juices from fruit, add the pudding mix.
Blend with mixer until thickens slightly.
You will pour this over all your fruit.
You can use different fruit or add to what is here.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and beat a few minutes.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add apples, nuts and flavoring.
Bake in a large, buttered pie plate at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine
corn,	milk
and melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients and
turn into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serves 12.

title: sacramento beef pot roast
directions: Trim all excess fat from meat. Brown beef in its own fat in a large skillet; remove and set aside. Drain all but 2 Tbsp. fat from skillet. Saute onion in fat until soft. Place meat, vegetables and seasonings in slow cooker; cover. Cook on low (190-200°) 10 hours, or on high (290-300°) 5 hours, or until meat is tender when pierced with a fork. Place meat and vegetables on a heated platter and keep warm. Turn heat control to high. Combine flour and water in a cup; pour into liquid in slow cooker; cover. Cook 15 minutes; pass sauce separately in a heated gravy boat. Serves 8.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in carrots while hot.
Beat eggs and put in carrots after cool.
Add flour and baking powder and cinnamon.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin in thin strips about 1/4-inch thick.
Put in saucepan with just enough water to cover.
Add 1 beef bouillon cube.
Cook over heat until just done (about 10 minutes).
Drain; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat. Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: christmas pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, 1/3 cup water and pumpkin.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Gradually beat into first mixture.
Stir in cherries and nuts; pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick and easy bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix in milk, salt and melted butter.
Stir in flour until not sticky. Cover and let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Pinch into 2 equal balls.
Place into bread pans or shape on cookie sheet.
Let rise and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chris' cherry supreme cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except eggs, at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat for 1 minute after each egg.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before turning out.

title: pineapple-lime punch
directions: Beat jelly until frothy. Add hot water and continue beating until jelly is dissolved. Add fruit juices.
Chill.
When ready to serve, pour over ice in punch bowl and add ginger ale. Garnish with orange slices and maraschino cherries. Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Remove from pan. Cool on rack.
Suitable for freezing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook linguini according to directions.
Chop tomatoes, cucumbers and shrimp.
Put a layer of linguini, a layer of tomatoes, cucumbers and shrimp and half bottle of Salad Supreme seasoning and half the Italian Zesty dressing.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Repeat layering and pour remaining salad seasoning and Italian Zesty dressing over layers.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Garnish with parsley and large shrimp.

title: broiled stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in small skillet. Add chopped mushroom stems and onion. Saute 4 to 5 minutes. Remove mixture to bowl. Add remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix well and set aside. Dip mushroom caps into reserved melted butter. Spoon about 1 to 2 teaspoons of filling into each mushroom cap.
Preheat pan with rack in high position.
Place stuffed mushrooms on rack with stuffing up. Broil 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken, celery, grapes, salt and mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with cashews.
Garnish with grapes.
Serve with Italian bread or crescent rolls.

title: zucchini relish(canning recipe)
directions: Combine zucchini, onions, green and red peppers and salt in large cooker; mix well and let stand overnight. Drain and rinse good with cold water. Add remaining ingredients and boil 20 to 30 minutes. Ladle into hot jars and adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes. Makes 6 pints.

title: trout almondine
directions: Clean and wipe, but do not wash, the trout after cutting into portion-size pieces.
Mix flour, salt, white pepper, m.s.g. and garlic powder.
Dredge trout pieces in seasoned flour.
Using a large, heavy frypan, heat 1/2 cup of the butter to bubbling point. Brown trout for 4 minutes on each side.
Put trout in a warm oven to keep hot.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Combine tea bags, cinnamon sticks, cloves, orange and lemon peels in boiling water.
Steep 20 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry juice cocktail.
Serve hot.
Makes six 1-cup servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown the beef and season with salt and pepper.
In a large saucepan, warm the refried beans, taco seasoning mix and water. Add salsa and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Scoop mixture into an ovenproof glass pan.
Sprinkle with onion, tomato and cheeses. Bake at 400° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pasta brie
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package.
Add olive oil and seasonings to whole tomatoes with juice.
Heat well.
Combine heated sauce with warm pasta.
Toss with Brie.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip and walnut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, stir together sugars, flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl mix together milk, butter, eggs and vanilla until blended.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add milk mixture and stir to combine.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups; grease the edges around cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Remove muffins from oven and cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: ribbon bologna wedges
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Spread evenly over bologna and sprinkle each piece with nuts.
Divide bologna into 2 stacks of 6 slices.
Garnish tops with parsley.
Cover both rolls with plastic wrap and chill.
At serving time, cut each stack into 16 wedges and insert a colored wooden pick in each wedge.

title: easy onion steak and potatoes
directions: Brown steak in oil.
In crock-pot, stir in 2 1/2 cups of water, beefy onion soup mix, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add meat and green beans in layers.
Cook all day on low.
Thicken with flour and 1/2 cup of water.

title: busy day casserole
directions: In bottom of casserole dish, put 1 cup dry rice.
Then layer hamburger meat.
Add stewed tomatoes, water, corn (do not drain), onion and pepper.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered, followed by 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, water and vanilla.
Blend until smooth. Quickly add chocolate and nuts.
Turn into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Spread and chill.

title: easy rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over lard, sugar and salt; let cool. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add eggs that have been slightly beaten to first mixture.
Add 2 cups of flour and then yeast and rest of flour.
Mix and put in refrigerator for 4 hours. Then make into rolls.

title: delicious double chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Whip with wisp until creamy. Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: sweet and pungent brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place brisket in baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover pan with foil. Cook in oven 3 to 4 hours.
(Meat should be sliced across the grain halfway through roasting time.)
Finger licking good!

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and roll into ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: salad
directions: Place all in large salad bowl in order given.
Top with chilled dressing.

title: marinated grilled chicken breasts
directions: In mixing bowl, whisk together orange juice concentrate, olive oil, honey, garlic, salt, pepper and lemon thyme.
Place chicken in a plastic container with a lid.
Pour marinade over chicken so that the chicken is coated.
Keep in refrigerator for 2 hours to overnight.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
This is a very large recipe, but recipe can be halved.

title: revolutionary war pound cake
directions: 1. Combine all cake ingredients, mix well. 2. Divide into 3 round 9-inch cake pans that have been greased

title: substitute for two or three eggs
directions: Substitute water, baking powder, oil and flour for each egg in recipes calling for 2 or 3 eggs. May substitute milk or other liquids for water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add all ingredients (except ham).
Beat until creamy.
Add shredded ham into mixture.
Roll into ball.

title: beef-cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add beef.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: floating island supreme(serves 8)
directions: Place paper cups in muffin pans.
Fill with ice cream. Sprinkle coconut over tops.
Freeze; serve frozen.

title: minted fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all the ingredients except fruit; stir until sugar dissolves.
Place fruit in large shallow dish; pour the mixture over.
Cover.
Chill 3 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Saute onions for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, oyster sauce, parsley and water.
Cover; cook 5 minutes until broccoli is tender.
Trim all visible fat from beef.
Broil thin slices.
Add meat and vermicelli to skillet.
Cook; stir until meat is heated, about 1 minute.

title: 2-minute fudge(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all of dry ingredients).
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
If all butter has not melted in cooking, it will as mixture is stirred.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into wax paper lined 8 x 4 x 3-inch dish.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer.
Cut in squares.

title: hash brown baked potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo.
Combine with soup and sour cream.
Add all other ingredients and stir in potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick beef and vegetable stew
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except peas. Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add peas and continue cooking 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Crush to make 1 3/4 cups crushed berries.
If measure is short, add water to berries.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Place cored and peeled apples in large baking pan.
Mix butter, sugar and apple pie spice.
Divide evenly and put into center of apple.
Wrap each apple in pie crust and sprinkle with remaining spice and sugar mix.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and pineapple. Add nuts and Cool Whip; then add dry pistachio pudding mix. Mix well and chill overnight.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Mix until well blended.
Place in an 8-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into bite size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chive cheese spread
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt and cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in milk and continue cooking and stirring until sauce thickens and boils, 1 minute.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve hot over cabbage.

title: fastnacht kuecheles
directions: Put flour into large pan and let stand at room temperature until lukewarm.
Push to sides of pan and make a well in the center.
Soften yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 3/4 cup of milk. Pour into flour.
Let stand in well until foamy, then add remaining sugar and melted fat.
Work ingredients to a dough, adding a little more flour, if necessary.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until light.
Turn onto a floured board and roll about half an inch thickness.
Cut in diamond or squares and let stand on board until very light.
If kitchen is very warm, this will not be too long.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan; line bottom of pan with waxed paper.

title: super scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and set.

title: dijon potato salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover and chill.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Bring water to the boil. Add raisins and boil for 5 minutes. Stir in sugar; reduce heat to medium. Combine cornstarch and cold water and stir into mixture. Stir in next 4 ingredients and cook until thickened. Stir in vinegar. Serve sauce warm over cooked ham.

title: low-fat cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cheese, liquid Butter Buds, Egg Beaters, garlic powder and Tabasco.
Stir in chopped green chilies if desired.
Pour into large glass casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Yields 12 to 24 servings.
Fat 2.2 g, cholesterol 2.1 mg; calories 79, carbohydrates 8.3 g; protein 6.3 g; sodium 171 mg.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce and spices. Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Wash squash and slice lengthwise.
(I peel mine.)
Mix egg, cottage cheese and flour.
Set aside. Parboil squash 3 minutes; drain.

title: fruit cake
directions: Place all ingredients in order in a large bowl.
Be sure to include any water left in the raisins and currants after boiling. Mix with a medium beater until well mixed.
Bake at 350° in a greased ring pan or 2 to 3 loaf pans.

title: sunshine jello salad
directions: Dissolve orange jello in hot water according to package directions. Stir in carrot. Set bowl in refrigerator to chill. Meanwhile, dissolve lemon jello with 1 cup hot water. Stir in cold water. Stir in pineapple and set on counter to cool.

title: punch
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together and cook 5 minutes.
Mix jello as directed and add to mixture.
Put in large or small containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer and let thaw to a slush.
Add a quart or more of ginger ale.
Serves 35 cups.

title: easy banana pudding(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine condensed milk with water.
Add pudding mix and beat one minute. Fold in La Creme.
Spoon one cup of pudding mix into a 2 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Top with vanilla wafers, then bananas. Repeat layers 2 times, ending with pudding.

title: fred's doritos casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, soup, Ro-Tel and onions.
Grate cheese and set aside.
In a large bowl you can bake in, put a layer of Doritos, then add layer of ground beef mixture, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat again, ending up with a layer of ground beef mix and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 12 minutes at 375°.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring until mixed.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight.

title: sunrise salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine gelatin and water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Combine pineapple and banana with gelatin; top with marshmallows and chill until set.

title: heavenly dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until smooth and thick.
Cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream. Delicious with fresh fruit.

title: toffee squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, yolk and vanilla; stir in flour and salt until blended.
Pack into rectangular 9 x 13-inch greased baking sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove; immediately apply crumbled chocolate bar.

title: new orleans pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter, sugar, syrup and salt; mix well.
Add pecans and vanilla; blend.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until a silver knife comes out clean when inserted in center of filling.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese well. Whip in sugar, vanilla and eggs (one at a time).
Mix 2 cups of cheese mixture with melted chocolate.
Grease large pie pan or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in plain mixture and swirl in chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or less.
Do not overbake. Chill.
This is a crustless cheesecake.

title: chop meat and cheese casserole
directions: In a pan, brown beef; drain.
Add onion, sauce, chili powder and garlic; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Separate biscuits; pat 5 on bottom of an ungreased casserole dish.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg.
Mix well.
Mix together meat and sour cream mixtures.
Pour on biscuits.
Arrange rest of biscuits on top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer 1 can green beans on bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle minced garlic over beans.
Cover with cheese mixes.
Layer bread crumbs.
Pour olive oil over bread crumbs.
Salt and pepper as needed or desired.
Pour small amount of water to wet bottom of dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: peanut butter fudge brittle
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, white chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons butter in double boiler.
Add pretzels and nuts.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spread, cool, break and store in tin.

title: no-fat fruit dessert
directions: Take cake out of its wrapping and place on a cake dish.
With a serrated edged knife, slice the top 1/2 to 3/4 inch off the cake and put aside.
Cut inside the cake 1/2 inch from each side, being careful not to cut all the way through to the bottom of the cake.
Then pull out a tunnel all around the inside of the cake.

title: granny berrier's blackberry dumplings
directions: Combine blackberries, sugar and lemon extract.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: turkish delight
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth; set aside. In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread one roll chocolate chip cookie dough. Spread cream cheese mixture on top of dough.
Cover with remaining cookie dough by patting pieces of cookie dough with hands and laying it on top of cream cheese.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick (really thick).
Add to cheese mixture and blend in.
Pour into container and refrigerate.

title: easy mints
directions: Combine margarine and water.
Place over low heat until margarine melts.
Remove from heat; add salt and extract. Gradually add sugar, blending until desired consistency is reached.
Knead until smooth.
Add a few drops of the food coloring before kneading.
(You can divide this and make several colors.)
Roll and slice.
Makes 1 pound of mints.
Does not keep for long period of time.
Very good.

title: lincoln cheese log
directions: Blend cheeses and horseradish, chill.
Form into log.
Coat with pecans.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Serve with rye crackers or party rye bread.

title: beef, beans and rice
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and rice, brown slightly. Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven until rice is done and most of moisture is absorbed.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corey's peanut butter bars
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and brown sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Spread into an 8 x 8-inch pan, greased well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wonderful cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place package of rolls in pan.
Mix sugar, pudding, pecans and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Pour melted butter on top.
Let set overnight or about 7 hours.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easy lemon coolers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in a large bowl.
Dough may be mixed by hand since it is like cookie dough and very thick.
Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix the onion and peppers in a large bowl with the carrots. Heat the remaining ingredients together until sugar is dissolved and smooth.
Pour over carrots.
Cover well; refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: baked chicken thighs
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan place preserves, dressing and soup mix. Mix and heat slowly.
Layer thighs in single layer.
Bake at 400°, turning every 20 minutes or so, in uncovered pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Tilt pan to remove fat.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add two eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add remaining eggs and flour alternately.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir together salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix gently.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chuck box chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing and egg.
Set aside. Rinse chicken with water and drain.

Dredge chicken in flour mixed with salt and pepper. Dip in dressing and egg mixture. Roll in cornflake crumbs. Arrange chicken pieces in foil lined broiler pan. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar together.
Mix beaten eggs, banana and
lemon
juice together; add to shortening mixture. Gradually add dry ingredients while mixing.
Add chopped nuts. Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla to milk.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, then milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Prepare all items.
Heat 12-inch skillet to 400°.
Best if cooked at table with electric skillet.
Melt suet and grease pan evenly.
Add beef slowly until cooked and push aside in pan.
Add soy, sugar and stock.
Allow to heat.
Add other ingredients and cook.
Add liquid as needed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and bell pepper.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Allow to cook 5 minutes.
Slice and salt eggplants, then fry in a small amount of oil.
Arrange slices of eggplant and sauce alternately in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Whip eggs and cheese together.
Pour over casserole and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix sugar, water, soy sauce, pineapple juice, oil, garlic and ginger powder.
Saturate chicken wings good.
Keep in refrigerator overnight or at least 8 hours.
Shake well periodically.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Bring margarine, sugar and milk to a full rolling boil in heavy 4-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching. Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Roll in balls and dip in sugar.
Press flat with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hal's black bean dream soup
directions: Saute carrots, onion, celery and pepper in olive oil.
Add beans and chicken broth.
Add all spices.
Simmer 2 hours plus or minus.
Add ham or kielbasa.
Simmer 38 minutes.
Puree 1/2 of soup and return.
Serve with parsley and sour cream.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Beat the first 9 ingredients in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth and fluffy.
Make a topping of the brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cream butter and sugars, add egg and vanilla. Mix flour and baking soda together and add to the mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto the cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes or until browned.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Roll out bread dough as for nut roll (do not let dough raise). Mix the egg, oregano, parsley and garlic salt; spread on rolled out dough, then sprinkle with cheese and pepperoni.
Roll up as nut roll and place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush roll with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix
eggs,
corn syrup, melted chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla
until
well blended.
Stir in pecans and pour in shell. Bake
at
for
50 to 60 minutes.
Pie is done if knife comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars, salt, egg and peanut butter in order.
Mix together baking soda and flour and blend into peanut butter mixture.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Press with fork.
Bake at 400° for ten minutes.

title: rice cake ricotta
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with mixer on medium.
See recipe for crust to follow.
Bake in 10-inch pie plate at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter.
Put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together eggs, 2 sticks butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat mixture for 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Spread sliced bananas over mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas. Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon stuff
directions: Whip cream; add Eagle Brand and lemon juice; pour into crust and chill.

title: crazy crust cherry pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, water, shortening and egg.
Blend well at low speed. Spread batter in a 9-inch pie dish. Carefully spoon filling into center of batter.
Do not stir. Bake 35 minutes at 425°.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Blend.
When well blended, chill and serve as needed.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add yolks, well beaten; cut in whites, beaten stiff.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes in moderate oven.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine chicken stock, carrots, celery, onions and oregano.
Bring to a boil over medium high heat.
Lower heat to medium and simmer for about 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside for 5 minutes.
Cut or shred into bite size pieces.
While chicken is cooling, stir noodles into stock, cook until noodles are tender.
Stir in parsley and chicken.
Low-fat.

title: beans and beef
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts (boil in water for 30 minutes) and cut in bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Mix soup, water chestnuts, butter, curry and lemon in saucepan over medium heat until heated through. Place some sauce in bottom of casserole.
Layer chicken, broccoli and sauce until all used up.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until heated through.

title: chocolate feather cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix in other ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in the reserved pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Combine butter with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in bowl in a saucepan. Mix water, shortening, oleo and cocoa. Bring to a boil. Pour over dry mixture. Mix well. Add eggs, milk, soda and vanilla. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: east india salad
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, orange peel, salt and curry powder.
Chill.
Pare, section and dice orange into a large bowl. Toss lightly with yogurt mixture and add remaining ingredients. Chill before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shirley's salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Buzz on and off until vegetables are in tiny pieces and mixture blended.
Store in refrigerator.
It just gets better.

title: ramen noodle cabbage salad
directions: Combine all salad ingredients in large bowl.
Combine all dressing ingredients in separate bowl and shake well.
Our over cabbage mixture.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Divide into 6 equal portions, shaping each into a 1-inch thick patty. Coat an electric skillet with vegetable cooking spray; heat to 320°.
Add patties and cook 5 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels; set aside and keep warm.
(I put them in the oven on warm.)

title: marshmallow rice krispie treats
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat; keep on low heat. Dip marshmallow in hot mixture.
Roll in Rice Krispies.
Put on wax paper covered cookie sheet and refrigerate until caramel hardens.
Makes between 50 and 60 treats.

title: southwestern corn bread
directions: In a food processor or blender, coarsely chop corn; set aside. In a bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking soda and salt. In a small bowl, combine egg, egg whites, milk and oil. Stir into dry ingredients until moistened. Add cheese, chilies and corn. Pour into a 9-inch square baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Serve warm.

title: cracker jacks
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, Karo and oleo. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add peanuts to mixture and coat well.
Add soda and vanilla.

title: chicken salad filling
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Add lettuce to each sandwich.

title: squash casserole
directions: Salt and cook sliced squash and onions over medium heat with no water.
Mash and drain.
Add sour cream, pimentos, soup and carrots.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with stuffing.
Line bottom of casserole dish with stuffing.
Pour other ingredients over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions in butter and oil in large pot. Add meat. Brown well. Add garlic, vegetables, salt and pepper as you brown meat. When browned, sprinkle mixture with flour; simmer for a few minutes.

title: cream cheese all butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup Bundt pan.
Beat butter and cream cheese until well blended; add sugar to cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla. Sift together flour and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out onto wire rack and cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: bailey's irish creme
directions: Place all ingredients, except whipping cream, in bowl.
Beat well.
Add whipping cream.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg and molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well and chill for 3 hours or overnight.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in powdered sugar and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: chicken wrapped in bacon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef. Wrap the chicken breast with bacon strips and place on top of dried beef.
Mix together sour cream and soup and pour mixture evenly

title: southwest meat loaf
directions: Mix together; pack into a loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in 10 x 16-inch Brown-in-Bag and place in baking dish.
Add bouillon, pineapple and juice, green pepper strips and onion slices to bag.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and soy sauce.
Mix until smooth and pour into bag.
Turn bag gently to mix ingredients well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place meatballs in single layer in bag.
Close bag.
Puncture top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugars.
Stir in egg, water and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, oatmeal, chocolate chips and raisins.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sausage stuffing broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook sausage until browned and no longer pink, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Mix with Hawaiian Punch and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale when serving.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat the eggs well; add the salt, milk and sugar and beat in the flour and baking powder with enough corn meal to form a soft batter; bake in shallow well-greased pans in a moderate oven about half an hour.
The exact quantity of corn meal cannot be given; usually about two cups will be sufficient.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until browned.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, herbs, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slice zucchini lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half of the zucchini slices in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Salt lightly.
Beat Ricotta or cottage cheese with egg; spread on zucchini.
Top with half the cheese mixture and half of the sauce.
Layer with remaining zucchini, cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Pre-heat oven 350°.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly and zucchini is tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook hamburger and onion until brown (drain).
Add salt and pepper.
Spread in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Put the rest of ingredients in blender on high for 15 seconds.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mexican chicken roll-ups
directions: Pound chicken breasts out flat.
In middle, put 1/2 to 1 whole green chile on chicken breast.
Cover pepper with cheese and 1/8 to 1/4 teaspoon cilantro.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat
oil
and sugar together;
add eggs and beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir into batter.
Add remaining
ingredients and stir to blend.
Pour into buttered, floured
tube
pan.
Bake
at
350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan.
Makes 2 small or 1 large cake.

title: oreo delight
directions: Chop Oreo cookies fine; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make sure bottom is covered.
Drip chocolate syrup over cookies.
(Reserve some syrup for top.)
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip together; pour over cookies.
Sprinkle with peanuts, then drip more chocolate. Freeze before serving.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well; drop by spoonful.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: seven-layered salad
directions: Tear half lettuce and put in the bottom of bowl.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Add the sliced hard-boiled eggs, then add the peas.
Tear other half of lettuce; layer on top of peas.
Crumble the bacon, then add the grated Swiss cheese.
Cover completely with mayonnaise.
Put onions on top (chopped).
Sprinkle paprika on top of onions.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: fruit delight
directions: Make jello as directed.
Chill until thickens; fold in cocktail, then chill!

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat well one egg. Beat in buttermilk and soda. Then beat in flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and oil and mix well. Heat griddle and grease well. Pour from spoon slightly apart. Turn pancake as soon as they are puffed and bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cookie mix
directions: Layer ingredients into jar in order given.
Press each layer firmly before adding the next ingredient.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and egg until light.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating.
Add corn meal and blend thoroughly.
Add cream and butter, mixing well and finally the grated lemon peel.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
This will make 8 tarts or a 9-inch pie.

title: fruit pudding delight
directions: Layer on bottom of a big deep dish or bowl first the angel food cake, pudding, Cool Whip and then fruit (strawberries). Repeat angel food cake, pudding, Cool Whip and then fruit (blueberries). Last layer whatever is left of angel food cake, pudding and Cool Whip, then fruit (raspberries).

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: louisiana yam cornbread
directions: Sift flour with cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and oil in large bowl; beat until smooth.
Add yams; beat until blended.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 425°
for 35 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Combine crabmeat, soups and bouillon. Let come to a boil and add 1/2 cup sherry wine.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Careful not to overbake.)
Let cool and store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: chocolate frosted ice cream roll
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line pan with paper; grease paper and set pan aside.
Sift first 4 ingredients together; set mixture aside.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; stir in flavorings.
Fold yolk mixture into egg white mixture, then gently fold in flour mixture.
Spread batter evenly in the prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: brisket rub(for 3 to 5 pound brisket)
directions: Mix all ingredients except for black pepper.
Add enough pepper to make a paste.
Rub paste thoroughly over brisket (excess fat trimmed away).
Wrap in HEAVY aluminum foil.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 225° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Put on wax paper and put in refrigerator.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix over medium heat with butter, milk, sugar, cocoa, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil. Boil one minute at a full boil. (Time it, too little time they won't set well, and too much boiling they are too hard). Remove from heat, after one minute and add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups oatmeal and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir well, then place by teaspoon full into waxed paper until set.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients like pie crust.
Divide in half and roll for bottom of 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Place apple slices on crust.
Mix last 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil until slightly thickened.
Pour over apples.
Roll out second crust. Place over apples.
Make a few slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost while still warm with a thin powdered sugar icing.

title: oriental shrimp appetizer
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper until soft.
Add mushrooms. Mix all ingredients together except crumbs.
Spoon into casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: cucumber sour cream salad
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Chill.
Mix sour cream with remaining ingredients.
Drain cucumbers thoroughly; add to sour cream and mix well.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring often until boiling. Let cook about 20 to 30 minutes or until syrupy, stirring often. Spoon boiling fruit into sterile jars and seal immediately.

title: yummy refrigerator dessert
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix 1/2 of the crumbs with 2 tablespoons melted butter and spread in bottom of 8 or 9-inch square Pyrex dish.
Beat eggs until frothy and add confectioners sugar, vanilla and 1/2 cup softened butter.
Place egg mixture over crumbs; sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over egg mixture.
Top nuts with pineapple.
Top pineapple with 1/2 pint stiffly beaten whipped cream.
Sprinkle rest of cookie crumbs over whipped cream. Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Top each serving with maraschino cherry.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until cool. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add salt and water.
Stir in flour to make very stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll thin.
Let dry for at least an hour, then roll up like a jelly roll and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Shake out strips and boil until done in chicken or beef broth.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased pan. Bake in 325° oven until light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: simmering potpourri
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To simmer, place 1/2 cup mixture and 2 cups water in a small saucepan on stovetop or in an electric potpourri pot.
Add more water as needed.

title: delicious white bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, salt, oil and water (the water must be very warm, 120° to 130°) in a large bowl.
Add 3 cups of the flour and mix with electric mixer until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Stir in additional flour and mix with large spoon until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.

title: hot crescent rolls
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Stir down in 3 parts. Roll out on floured board as pie crust; cut into eight sections (pie shape).
Roll wide edge into the point (like crescent rolls). Place on cookie sheet.
Let rise 6 hours (or less).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: squash and apple casserole
directions: Mix squash and apples in a 3-quart casserole.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and combine with brown sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Sprinkle over squash and apples.
Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until tender.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut into sliced and lay on 12-inch pizza pan covered with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Finely grate
vegies and mix well.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over vegies.
Toss well and chill.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and vinegar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add diced, cooked beets and let stand for 30 minutes. Pat with butter and serve.
Use more cornstarch if you prefer a thicker sauce.

title: double cheese
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In large skillet, cook meat, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese, then add noodles.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Slice tomato and arrange on top. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican ground beef
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat. (I add about 1/2 cup water. This makes the meat crumble real well. I then cook the water dry.) Drain. Add flour and seasonings. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes. Can be used for tacos, burritos, taco salad, etc.

title: shrimp potato stew
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, heat oil on medium setting.
Add onions and cook until brown.
Add shrimp and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in cubed potatoes, parsley, boiling water and salt and pepper. Cook for 60 minutes.
Serve over rice.
For better taste, boil shrimp peelings in water for shrimp stock.

title: frosted lime salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: best cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries, but reserve 3/4 cup juice.
Combine cherries, juice, sugar, tapioca, almond extract and red food coloring.
Put in a large 9 or 10-inch unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter and lattice topping.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add jello; cool until almost stiff.
Add strawberries.
Pour in pie shell, then chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli or winter mix until tender; drain.
Place into buttered 2-quart dish.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and Miracle Whip.
Pour over hot vegetables.
Toss croutons with melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: easy coconut macaroons
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir in coconut, egg whites and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto a cookie sheet, coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet and let cool on a wire rack.
Yields 1 dozen cookies.

title: hot rice
directions: Saute onions, celery, bell peppers, jalapeno peppers and garlic until tender.
Mix sausage in and cook until done.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine sausage/vegetable mixture, rice and soup.
Heat through.
Serves 12.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, onion and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Fry tortillas in hot oil until softened; drain.
Place rounded tablespoonful of meat sauce and cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Place seam side down in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: *hershey pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Add margarine and buttermilk with soda.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, eggs and melted chocolate.
Beat 1 minute.
Add pecans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim away any excess fat from steak and cut into 1/4 slices. Heat a large skillet until very hot with about 1 tablespoon butter and swirl to coat bottom of pan.
Pan fry beef strips, a few at a time, 1 minute on each side or until steak is as done as you like it.
Add remaining butter to skillet and stir in onions.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Push to 1 side, stir in mushrooms and saute for 3 minutes.
Add beef broth and salt and simmer 5 minutes.

title: creamy chipped beef casserole
directions: Snip beef in bite size pieces.
Brown in Crisco until edges curl; drain.
Mix milk and soup.
Add beef, hash browns and 1/2 can onion rings.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove lid.
Crumble remainder of onion rings over top.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 450°.

title: polish babka
directions: Scald milk, add sugar and butter.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast with a little of the warm milk mixture in bowl and then add to remaining milk mixture.
Add one half of the flour and beat well. Add salt to eggs and beat until thick.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add the rest of the flour, orange and lemon rind.
Knead for 15 minutes, then add the raisins and nuts.
If dough is sticky, add more flour.
Cover and let rise in a greased bowl until double in bulk.

title: confetti macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain well. Combine macaroni, Spam, cheese, green pepper and onion.
Stir well and chill. Combine mayonnaise, milk, vinegar and salt.
Pour over macaroni salad and toss well.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain and cool.
Put a layer of lasagna noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan and then add 1/3 of hamburger or pork on that layer, then 1/3 of the sauce, 1/3 of cottage cheese and 1/3 of the Mozzarella.
Do this 3 times, so you should have 3 layers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place chicken in a bowl.
Pour 1/2 bottle of hot sauce over chicken.
Toss and let sit for 10 minutes, then toss again.
