Put drummettes in a baking pan and pour barbecue and the other half of hot sauce, then pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350°, covered, for 35 minutes and uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli chowder - the bounty
directions: Cook broccoli, covered, in 1 can of chicken broth until tender.
Remove broccoli from broth and chop coarsely.
Add milk, cream, ham, salt, pepper and dry mustard to broth and broccoli. Simmer and stir occasionally.
Saute onions and potato in butter. Add the other can of chicken broth and cook until soft.
Add the potato mixture and the remaining ingredients to broccoli; heat just to serving temperature.
Serves 6 or more, if using smaller servings to accompany sandwich, etc.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli, using florets only.
Add chopped onion and bacon pieces.
Toss.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until well blended.
Stir into broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In covered pan, cook potatoes in salted water about 20 minutes.
While potatoes are cooking, brown beef with onion and drain off fat.
Add beans, soup, water, salt & pepper.
Mix together, place in 2-quart casserole dish and set aside.
When potatoes are done, mash while still hot, stir in egg and add enough milk to make fluffy.
Season with salt & pepper and spread over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Slice Italian bread lengthwise and place on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Spread with softened butter and sprinkle with garlic salt and basil.
Top with shredded Mozzarella.
Bake until crust is lightly browned and cheese is melted.

title: cherry-dump cake
directions: Layer as listed.
May add 1 cup coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese onto a large plate or platter.
Pour the seafood sauce over the cream cheese and spread evenly.
Next, put the olives over the seafood sauce.
Finally, top it off with the shrimp.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: boo and boo's favorite cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk; make into a batter.
Pour into pan of melted butter and pour in fruit.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Cut sausages in half, crosswise.
Wrap each in 1/2 strip of bacon, securing with a toothpick.
Place one layer in the bottom of a crock-pot and cover with a layer of brown sugar.
Repeat until all sausages are used, ending with sugar.
Cook on low setting for about 4 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

Do not attempt to bake at a higher temperature or the brownies will burn. Generously grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine chocolate and butter in a medium saucepan, over low heat, stirring constantly until the chocolate is nearly melted. Remove from heat and stir until smooth.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in double boiler.
Pop popcorn and put into a large bowl.
Pour marshmallow mixture onto popcorn; mix in M&M's and peanuts.
Press into large, greased pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: sweet onion pockets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls.
On lightly floured board, separate rolls into 4 rectangles each, making a total of eight.
Press perforated edges together.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of mixture over half of each roll.
Fold edges together.
Press edge with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: the best pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add the flour.
Bake in a large, greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pizza snack
directions: Toast bread.
Put tomato, seasonings and cheese on toast. Broil for 1 to 5 minutes.
Good with salad.
Equals 1 bread, 1 fat, 1 meat, 1/2 vegetable exchange on diabetic diet.

title: crock-pot texas hash
directions: Brown beef, drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir thoroughly, cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (on high for 4 hours).
Serve with garlic and tossed salad.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Dice shrimp and set aside.
Cook onion in margarine; add water, potatoes and seasonings.
Cover and cook 15 minutes until tender.
Add milk, flour and shrimp.
Stir over low heat until thickened and shrimp are heated through.

title: zucchini bread(two 9 x 5-inch loaves)
directions: Stir until well blended.
Add 1 cup nuts (walnuts).
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.

title: amaretto cocoa mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine all ingredients; stir until well blended.
Store in airtight container.
Yields about 19 1/2 cups cocoa mix.

title: sherry and miss jessie's parson's rolls
directions: Mix
soda
and	dissolved yeast in buttermilk.	Combine with other
ingredients	and
knead.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet.
Let dough warm to room temperature (or may be placed in oven immediately).
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add creamed mixture to pudding mixture.
In food processor, crush one package Oreo cookies.
Layer pudding and crushed Oreos.
Save enough cookies to put on top.
Can put Gummy worms through or on top or silk flower.

title: country meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 of tomato sauce.
Form meat loaf shape in a shallow baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: *One cup of butter-flavored Crisco can be substituted for oleo and shortening.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream together oil, eggs and sugar.
Add food coloring and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend with egg mixture. Add strawberries all at once and mix well.
Stir in nuts.

title: jalapeno cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fold 6-inch piece of aluminum foil in half; fold edges up to make a tray.
Place nuts, chili powder and cumin in tray; place on baking sheet.
Bake nut mixture for 6 minutes, until fragrant and begins to darken.
Let cool.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine milk and egg.
Add biscuit mix, onion and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on batter.
Pour melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Slice loaves lengthwise into layers.
Make filling of cheese, cream, sugar and extract.
Spread on bottom layers.
Top with pie filling, then remaining cake layers, next another layer of filling and then the balance of pie filling. Chill.
Ice sides of cakes with Cool Whip.
Do not ice tops.
Makes 2 loaf cakes.

title: heinz orange chicken glaze
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush on chicken or fish when grilling or broiling.

title: swedish beef stew
directions: In heated Dutch oven, melt butter and 2 tablespoons margarine. Brown the beef.
Remove meat, add 1 tablespoon margarine and cook chopped onion 10 minutes.
Add coffee, broth, brown sugar and anchovies.
Bring to a boil.
Add meat and spices.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Thicken with flour-water paste. Serves 4.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and almond bark in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool before touching.

title: curried chicken log
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth with Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, red hot pepper sauce and curry powder.
Add celery, parsley and 2 tablespoons almonds.
Blend in chicken.
Shape into a roll about 8 inches long on wax paper.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, roll in remaining chopped almonds.
Place on serving platter; garnish with parsley and place crackers around log.
Makes 10 servings.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, eggs and salt.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls; flatten on cookie sheet with cup dipped in flour.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350°. Delicious.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar, 1/2 cup granulated sugar, vanilla and eggs and beat until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Chill until firm enough to roll.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and 8 ounces of cheese.
Put 4 ounces of cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs.
Put bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diabetic homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add Pet milk, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla flavoring. Stir until mixed well.
Pour in freezer container and finish filling with 2% milk.
Freeze in hand or electric freezer and serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: granola
directions: In a separate bowl, blend the water, oil, honey, vanilla and salt.
Add liquid to dry and mix. Spread on 2 greased cookie sheets. Bake 1 hour or until dry and golden. When cool, add raisins, dates, almonds, etc.
Store in covered containers.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, oranges and pineapple.
Blend salad oil, orange juice, vinegar, salt and marjoram.
Add chicken mixture; chill for at least 1 hour.
Drain if necessary.
Add mayonnaise and toss.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients and put into crumb crust pie shells.
Bake on 425° for 15 minutes, then on 275° for 1 hour.
Let sit in oven overnight.

title: millionaire turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Add pecans and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto heavily buttered cookie sheet. Chill in freezer.

title: old fashioned cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Cut in shortening until well blended.
Combine egg and milk in small bowl until well blended.
Add egg mixture to dry mixture.
Mix well. Pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Beat pumpkin until well blended.
Add sugar and flour; blend until smooth. Add eggs and beat. Add spices and milk.
Stir in melted butter and mix well.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in hot 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: sugar glazed cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough at a time and form into balls.
Dip top half in ice water, then in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
With finger press down the center of each ball.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: jack pot casserole
directions: Brown
meat; add onion.
Cook until golden.
Add tomato soup, water and noodles;
cook until noodles are tender.
Stir often. Season
to
taste.
Add
corn and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter mint salad
directions: Mix dry jello with pineapple; mix well.
Add marshmallows and mints.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: creamed spinach
directions: On stove top in medium size pot, melt 2 tablespoons butter, then add 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of garlic powder.
Mix well, then add the cup milk.
On medium heat, keep stirring until mixture thickens and then add thawed spinach and mix well again.
(Add 1 hard-boiled egg, optional.)
Cook a few minutes longer and serve.

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, spices, salt and ginger.
Beat in 2 slightly beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, egg and weakened vinegar in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool completely and pour over sliced bananas and chopped nuts.

title: holiday champagne punch
directions: Put frozen block of strawberries in punch bowl.
Pour white wine over strawberries.
Let sit until strawberries are thawed. Immediately prior to serving, gently add champagne.
Stir gently. When serving, make sure each glass gets a piece of strawberry.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix sugar, water and liquified bananas, lemonade and juices together.
Freeze in Ziploc bag, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving time.
Remove from Ziploc bag and place in a large bowl.
Pour ginger ale over frozen chunk.
As this starts to thaw, it makes a real good slushy drink.

title: sharon's cran-apple crunch
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and raisins and put in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: aunt margaret's cookies
directions: Beat eggs, milk and soda.
Add sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Add blended flour and baking powder.
Bake, dropped on greased cookie sheets, 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: bean pie
directions: Cook navy beans until tender and can be mashed with a fork. Drain beans in strainer; place beans in blender while warm with milk and melted butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Add spices, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch
pan.
Sprinkle
brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain fruit, arrange
pineapple slices and maraschino cherry halves on sugar mixture.
Mix
cake
as
directed
on the label with water,
eggs and
1/2 cup margarine.
Do not substitute fruit juice
for water.
Beat as directed.
Pour batter over fruit. Bake at
375° for
about
minutes
until
tests done with toothpick.
Let stand
5 minutes for topping to begin to set, then turn upside down on large plate.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: honey cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil and honey.
Beat until very thick. Combine dry ingredients and sift 3 times.
Combine pineapple juice and water, bring to a boil and add baking soda.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into lightly greased 10-inch tube pan lined with waxed paper on bottom.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool. Peel sweet potatoes and mash. Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients; stir sugar mixture and egg into mashed potatoes. Shape mixture around marshmallow and roll in corn flakes. Place in a single layer on a baking sheet. Cover and freeze 2 hours. Pour oil into a large skillet to depth of 1/2-inch; heat to 350°. Fry croquettes until golden brown, turning once.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Cover cucumbers and onions with 2 tablespoons salt and ice cubes and let stand for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Drain real good.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and slice apples and mix with the 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange this mixture in pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix ingredients together in order presented.
Cut shrimp down the middle.
Take out black vein.
Put stuffing in shrimp.
Place each shrimp in a muffin tin.
Bake for 10 minutes.
When no longer shiny, shrimp are done!

title: lasagna pizza
directions: Prepare a recipe of pizza sauce or use a jar of pizza sauce. Butter 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Arrange 10 lasagna noodles in pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese.
Cover with remaining noodles. Spread pizza sauce evenly over noodles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil.
Add water, wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to a full boil, separating broccoli pieces.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turketti
directions: Mix all together; put in flat pan or dish.
Top with cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups water, 1 cup sugar and oleo in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Add to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and transparent.
Beat egg yolks with milk and add a small amount of mixture into yolks.
Add yolk mixture to saucepan mixture, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and the lemon rind; cool slightly. Spoon into pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: danish sukkernodder
directions: Beat sugar and butter.
Add flour; knead.
Roll into filbert-sized balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate donuts
directions: Combine and deep fat fry.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, egg and shortening together, then add the milk, flour, soda and vanilla.
Blend well, then add the rhubarb.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with a mixture of 1/3 cup brown sugar and the cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gold drop cookies
directions: Spread half of the crackers with peanut butter.
Top each with a second cracker.
In the top of a double boiler, melt butterscotch chips.
Dip sandwich cookies into butterscotch. Place on wax paper to set.
Yields 1 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion until tender in butter.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Drain mushroom liquid and add enough chicken broth to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add cream gradually, stirring until thickened. Add rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in margarine until clear; drain and set aside.
In iron Dutch oven, combine flour and oil.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until light brown (darker for darker gravy).
Add shrimp to roux; cook until pink. Add sauteed vegetables; cook and stir together for about 1/2 minute.
Add 1 quart water, stirring constantly.
When smooth, add salt, black pepper and red pepper to taste.
Simmer on low for about 20 minutes.
Add water if too thick.
Serve over rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to boil. Let boil 2 minutes and add rest of the ingredients.
Drop onto wax paper by the spoonful!
Let cool.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a large saucepan, mix butter, water and cocoa.
Heat to boiling.
Take off heat; add flour, sugar, salt, sour cream, baking soda and eggs.
Mix well and pour into 15 x 11-inch baking pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Pour icing over warm cake.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, softened margarine and peanut butter together.
Knead and shape into balls.
Place on tray on waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Melt shortening with chocolate chips.
Dip balls with a toothpick in chocolate 3/4 way. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Remove and store in a sealed container.

title: peanut butter pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add peanut butter. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.

title: asparagus and mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour 1 can of mushroom soup over chicken with 1/2 can water.
Cook for about 40 minutes.
While waiting, cook noodles following package directions.
Set aside. When chicken is done, place chicken on plate and mix noodles with cooked asparagus and mushrooms in casserole dish.
Add chicken on top of noodles and add last can of soup.
Heat in oven another 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove the yolks and mash. Combine chicken, egg yolks, celery, mustard, salt and mayonnaise; mix well.
Stuff the whites with mixture; sprinkle with paprika. Serves 12.

title: pizza pie
directions: Soften yeast in 2 teaspoons warm water.
Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk (1/2 hour).
Simmer remaining ingredients until dough is ready.
Add 2 cups fairly thick tomato gravy.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Pour on the sauce and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400°.

title: remoulade sauce for shrimp
directions: Mix well; add 1 cup salad oil.
You can use blender for this. Pour over boiled, peeled shrimp and serve on lettuce with crackers.

title: bean burgers
directions: Spread each 1/2 bun with butter, cover with beans and sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Top with strips of bacon.
Broil about 4-inches from flame until bacon is crisp.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Cut up onion and green pepper.
Combine ground beef, onion, green pepper and all remaining ingredients.
Put in pot or dutch oven.
Simmer 45 minutes or so.
Recipe may be doubled.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: broccoli and rice dish
directions: Boil broccoli until cooked.
Cook rice.
Add together with milk, soup and onion.
Heat dish in microwave or oven.

title: raw spinach salad
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Carefully wash spinach leaves through 3 or 4 waters.
Drain well and chill.
Shred coarsely with kitchen scissors and combine with tomatoes, green onions, celery and salt. Drizzle dressing over the top and toss lightly until vegetables are well coated with dressing.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg. Serve immediately on individual plates.
Makes 5 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Put into casserole.
Refrigerate a day or two or freeze.
Dice 2 sticks oleo on top and bake until bubbly hot in 350° oven, approximately 1/2 hour.
Bake uncovered.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Bake at 325° in 8 x 10-inch greased pan for 30 minutes.
Cool, cut in squares and roll in the powdered sugar.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients, then add crushed bananas.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/3 cup melted margarine and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on pretzel crust.
Mix strawberry jello, dissolved in 2 cups hot water, with strawberries and pineapple.
When partly set, pour over pretzel crust, cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind onions and peppers together.
Heat sugar, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Add onion and pepper mixture; cook for 3 minutes.
Fill hot sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints. Use water bath for 15 minutes.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Discard all but 4 tablespoons of the bacon drippings.
Add corn to frying pan and cook without stirring until bottom is well browned.
Add milk and seasonings, stirring until mixed thoroughly.
Cover and cook over low heat for approximately 10 minutes.
Arrange cooked bacon slices on top and serve.

title: scallop-rice salad
directions: Saute vegetables in olive oil.
Add sea scallops and cook until opaque (10 to 15 minutes).
Add lemon juice, vinegar, horseradish and hot sauce.
Mix with cooked rice.
Serves 2.

title: lee's pancakes
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Add egg yolk, oil and water; blend.
Fold in the egg whites.
Cook in hot skillet on one side until bubbles appear.
Turn pancakes to other side and brown lightly.
Serve hot.
Any leftover batter may be used the next day if refrigerated until ready to use.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and margarine to rolling boil.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Beat in vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: company pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Trim fat.
Cook in oil in Dutch oven until brown; remove.
Mix remaining ingredients, except water, flour and lemon juice in Dutch oven.
Return beef to Dutch oven.
Cover and bake 3 hours and 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove to heated platter.
Skim fat from liquid.
Shake water and flour; gradually stir into liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in lemon juice; cook 1 minute.
Slice beef thinly.
Serve with gravy.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Mash potatoes; blend in butter, brown sugar, cinnamon-sugar and salt.
Add cream, beating potatoes until creamy and fluffy. Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows; broil 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: oriental fried rice
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Saute rice until golden (5 to 10 minutes).
Stir in onions, bacon, sesame seed, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Heat 5 minutes.
Add egg and blend well; cook about 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: quick fudge brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup of the chocolate pieces; stir in graham cracker crumbs, sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in remaining chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spread mixture in a well-greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack; cut into squares.
Makes 36.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together oil, eggs, cheese and onion, then add zucchini. Mix until well blended, then add Bisquick.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in square baking dish for about 30 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place 2 teaspoons of mix in a cup/mug and add hot water.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and oil until well mixed.
Add almond extract and eggs; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Gradually blend in all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar at low speed.
By hand, stir in almonds and brickle chips.
Chill, if desired.
Shape large tablespoonfuls of dough into balls; roll in sugar.
Place 5-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets; with fork dipped in sugar, flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown around edges.
Cool cookies 1 minute before removing from cookie sheets.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen (4-inch) cookies.
I make smaller cookies, rolling balls about 1-inch, makes 7 dozen small cookies.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with margarine, sugar and nuts.
Form a ball around 1 marshmallow, roll in crushed cornflakes.
Just before serving, warm sweet potato balls in a 350° oven 15 minutes or until marshmallow has softened.

title: fast dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well; drop by spoon into greased floured muffin cups.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding mix, butter, egg and milk.
Beat for two minutes at medium speed.
Pour mixture into bottom of greased 9-inch deep or 10-inch pie pan.
Arrange drained peach slices on top of batter. Shape like flower petals.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook meat, onions and green pepper until meat and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat and pour into 2-quart dish. Cover and bake 1 hour, ungreased.

title: finger paints
directions: Add enough water to cornstarch to make a paste.
Add into boiling water and stir until clear; cool.
Add soap flakes and powder.
Divide and add food coloring.
Store in airtight containers.

title: cheese pet
directions: Alternate bread and cheese in buttered casserole.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add milk, wine, mustard and salt.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese.
Let stand for several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Let casserole return to room temperature before baking for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix pizza sauce, tomato paste and water. Brown ground beef.
Make 3 layers of macaroni, beef, cheese sauce and pepperoni in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until onion is golden brown.
Put in slow cooker with all remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly; cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over hot buttered noodles or rice.

title: big lor's "excellent" shrimp scampi
directions: Clean shrimp.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish in oven.
Add salt, garlic and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer in the dish.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes, in oven at 400°.
Turn shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon peel and lemon juice.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: herbed black-eyed pea salad
directions: Cook peas in boiling salted water 15 to 20 minutes or until peas are tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water until cool. Drain well; set aside.
Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp. Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add garlic to drippings in skillet; saute 1 minute.
Add green onions and red pepper; saute until tender.
Cool completely. Combine bacon, pepper mixture, peas, mayonnaise, vinegar, oregano and pepper; stir well.
Serve at room temperature.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix 1 cup Quick Oats and 1 1/2 cup boiling water and set aside.

title: scrumptious chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients and beat for 1 minute.
Pour into pan and bake 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mckenley pie
directions: Combine ingredients and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Top will be crusty on top when it is done. Makes 1 pie.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square or round baking pan.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients and cook until hot.
Garnish with 1/2 cup grated cheese, 1/4 cup diced olives and diced onion.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix whipped topping with milk; add lemonade.
Whip until smooth.
Pour into crust and chill overnight or 4 hours minimum.

title: hash browns with fried onion rings
directions: Butter dish.
Add hash browns, milk, soup and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place onion rings and Cheddar cheese on top; bake 5 minutes more, or until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the margarine (melted), graham cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar in a large heavy saucepan.
Add peanut butter, coconut and vanilla.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut. To make the glaze for the balls, melt chocolate and paraffin wax in top of a double boiler with boiling water in the bottom.
Using a fork, carefully dip each ball into the glaze and place on wax paper to harden.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Beat together pudding and milk.
Refrigerate 5 minutes.
Add pumpkin and spice.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 10 minutes before serving.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cut
turkey into small pieces.
Put into baking dish or pan. Add
soup and milk.
Put moist stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serve.

title: cheese dip or spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 1 hour. Roll into ball; put chopped pecans on outside. Place in small bowl. This ball is softer than most.

title: lime-pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O by package directions and place in freezer until firm.
Place Pet milk can in freezer.
You only want to chill the milk so it will whip up.
Do not freeze the milk.
After it chills and Jell-O is firm, place milk in chilled glass bowl and whip to firm consistency.
Add whipped cream to Jell-O and fold until Jell-O is broken into small pieces.
Add some grated cheese and pecan pieces and fold together, then place in icebox until needed. Good with chicken dressing and holiday meals.

title: chocolate marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Cool; beat eggs.
Add sugar, chocolate and butter mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and flour with baking powder.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour a large jar of marshmallow cream over hot brownies.
Place under broiler until lightly browned (2 to 3 minutes).
Cool and top with chocolate icing.

title: granola bars
directions: Place oats in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at
for
15 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals; set aside.
Combine
remaining
ingredients; add oats, and mix well. Spread
mixture
evenly
into
lightly greased jellyroll pan. Bake
at
for
25 minutes.
Cool completely and cut into bars.
Yields about 5 dozen bars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll in shape of a ball or can pat in a shallow dish.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together stuffing seasoning packet, soup and broth.
Put half of dry stuffing mix in bottom of casserole baking dish.
Add layer of chicken.
Pour half of soup mixture over chicken.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cold tuna salad
directions: After pasta has cooled and peas thawed, mix all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency. Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Combine shortening, butter, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: renkin
directions: In a double saucepan, combine soup, cheese, onion and green pepper.
Cook slowly until cheese is melted and onion and green pepper are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add egg, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.
An excellent Sunday night dish.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Heat milk and flour until hot.
Add cheese and heat until melted and thick.
Mix Ritz crackers with melted butter.
Cook veggies.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, place veggies.
Pour sauce over and spread.
Place cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. To reheat, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: violet duggin's chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until done with salt, pepper, water and margarine.
Skin chicken; take off bone.
Cut in small pieces. Add chicken broth to chicken.
Add finely chopped onion and celery.
Add 2 beaten eggs, bread crumbs and sage (fresh from garden if you have it).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Add Bisquick last.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch oblong Pyrex pan and bake until golden brown on top at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut into finger-size squares, about 40.
Can also be used as a main coarse with salad or as a vegetable dish.
Can be made ahead, refrigerated, then baked before serving.
Stays well on a warming tray.

title: stick cookies
directions: Melt chips; add nuts and noodles.
Drop on wax paper and chill.

title: boneless chicken italiano
directions: Cut chicken and red pepper in cubes.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients well.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Serve with Italian bread and salad.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Note:
Extra cheese may be used if desired.

title: chili tomatoes
directions: Layer tomato slices and green pepper rings in shallow glass dish.
Shake remaining ingredients, except lettuce, in tightly covered jar.
Pour onto vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: ham-stuffed manicotti
directions: Age fresh duck 3 to 5 days in refrigerator.
Bone duck breasts.
With breast bone up, slit meat along ridge of bone, gently scraping and cutting meat away from breast bone, making one perfect "fillet" from each side of breast.
(Bones may be used to make stock, if desired.)

title: cole slaw
directions: After cabbage is shredded, salt well.
Grate in carrots, add chopped green pepper and grate onion so that only juice is added. Shake together in a large jar.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, pickle juice and water (if necessary to moisten) through cabbage mixture.

title: meatballs with tomatoes and green peppers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into 3/4 inch meat balls. Put in pan with tomatoes and onions.
Blend together the soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Add to the pan and heat over medium-low heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 2 cups chopped green pepper.
Cook 10 minutes or until meat balls are done.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons.
Dip fork in a beaten egg and press down.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Fine cut peanuts can be added before cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Blend pears with juice and softened cream cheese in blender. Dissolve jello in 1 cup of water; add to other ingredients in blender.
Blend.
Pour in bowl or mold; place in refrigerator until set.

title: tomato and eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in water and salt (sliced); drain and mash. Blend eggs, pepper, onion, oregano and saltines.
Slice tomatoes and spread over top, then sprinkle cheese.
Bake in a buttered casserole for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in percolator.
In basket put the spices.
Makes 30 cups.

title: navy bean salad
directions: Cook beans with seasoning and salt; drain.
Add the other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cracklin cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix lightly. Grease iron frying pan (medium size). Cook until top and side are brown and crisp.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
For each serving, add 1 cup hot water to 1/3 cup cocoa mix.
Stir until blended.
Store remaining mix in airtight container.
Makes 28 servings.

title: freezer bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions; let stand 2 hours.
Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Mixture will be thick.
Drain cucumbers; sprinkle with celery seed.
Add syrup to cucumbers and freeze in plastic containers.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Pat crushed Oreos into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve approximately 1/2 cup crushed Oreos for topping.
Drizzle melted margarine evenly over cookies.
Refrigerate for about an hour.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Mix molasses, brown sugar, egg and shortening.
Add dry ingredients to make a soft dough.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll on floured board and cut with floured cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 375° oven for about 12 minutes.
Makes 18 (4-inch) dolls.

title: coffee souffle
directions: Pour strong coffee over the marshmallows.
Place over double boiler until they melt and mix well.
Let cool.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold the cream into the coffee-marshmallow mixture. Put in sherbet glasses.

title: french chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and melted chocolate. Beat into first mixture.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat one at a time.
Add a dash of salt.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped topping.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika and mix well.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of the mixture around each olive, covering it completely.
Arrange on baking sheet and freeze. Place in plastic bags and return to freezer.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill large salad bowl with shredded lettuce.
Add in layers: celery, onion, green pepper and peas.
Spread over with mayonnaise. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese over sugar, topping it with bacon.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix the rest together and pour over vegetables.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Drain all 3 cans of beans before you pour other part over it.

title: bake-a-roux
directions: Mix flour and oil together in a heavy ovenproof container. Place on center shelf in preheated 400° oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Set timer; stir roux every 15 minutes.
Roux should be a caramel color when done.
Remove from oven; cool.
Transfer to containers with tight fitting lids; store in refrigerator until needed.
Roux may also be frozen.
Yields enough roux for 4 to 6 pots of gumbo.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Add cooked broccoli.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat with oregano, salt and garlic in a separate saucepan.
Combine tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in heated sauce.
Use 3 tortillas for bottom layer in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put layer of meat, cheese and sauce, beginning with tortillas and ending with cheese and sauce.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix sugar and cornstarch together and add to eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Boil until thickened. Pour into prepared unbaked 9-inch crust.
Cover with top crust. Brush with milk and sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake in a 425° oven.

title: tiny meat pies
directions: Cook onions, peppers and chilies in oil with meat until meat is done, but not too brown.
Salt and pepper.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs and olives; season to taste.
Chill overnight, if possible. Prepare pie crusts.
Roll dough thinly.
Cut in 3-inch rounds. Place 1 tablespoon of filling on rounds and fold over; pinch together at edges with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes until brown.
Yields 90 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa, sugar, milk and salt.
Boil 2 1/2-3 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and drop onto wax paper.

title: meat filled manicotti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Cool in a single layer on foil.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown beef and sausage; drain fat.
Stir together meat, 1 cup Mozzarella, eggs, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each cooled pasta tube with 1/4 cup meat filling.
Spread a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place filled pasta in dish.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and add additional Parmesan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: skinny sour cream
directions: Blend cheese with a dash of lemon juice and enough milk to make consistency of sour cream.
Refrigerate until needed.
Yields 1 cup.

title: restaurant style potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pierce potatoes with a fork; microwave on High until they are soft, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half vertically.
Scoop out inside of potato, leaving 1/4-inch of potato shell remaining.
Heat oil to 365° in deep fryer or deep saucepan.
Place potatoes in hot oil; fry 5 minutes.
Drain potatoes on paper towel.
Fill potato shells with cheese and bacon bits.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Bake for 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boiling point.
Then add last 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop spoonfuls on tinfoil.
Let cool.
No baking needed.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in candies and nuts.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, press 3 to 4 additional M&M's into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may also press dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cook for about 15 minutes to make bars.

title: jalapeno cocktail pie
directions: Sprinkle onions, pepper and garlic in well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Cover with cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Cool.
Cut into squares or serve warm.
Can be frozen.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Let soak for 4 to 6 hours before cooking.
Great for deer meat.

title: chef salad supreme(this salad is scrumptious.)
directions: Clean lettuce and break into small pieces in a large bowl.
Add cabbage either grated or broken into small pieces.
Add cheese, cucumber, ham, olives and tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Top with egg slices and croutons.
Use your favorite dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce jumble cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, frost with following glaze.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Cook vermicelli in broth.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in onions and peppers; combine thoroughly.
Add chicken, tomatoes, mushrooms, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in peas.
If mixture appears dry, add liquids from peas and mushrooms or additional chicken broth.
Turn into a large, greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour or until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: spicey cabbage
directions: Shred the cabbage and slice the onion thinly.
Layer this in a bowl and sprinkle the sugar on top.
Heat the oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed, and salt.
When boiling pour this mixture over the top of the cabbage.
Cover and let stand for 4 to 6 hours, then mix and serve.

title: roquefort onion tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake crust 8 to 10 minutes.
Saute onions in oil until limp and golden.
Transfer with slotted spoon to crust, distribute evenly.
Sprinkle Roquefort over top.
Spoon egg and cream mix over and bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Note:
Varied dressings or other ingredients can be used.

title: ham salad filling
directions: Stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: doctor bird cake(banana-pineapple)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch tube pan.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add pineapple and juice, vegetable oil, vanilla, eggs and bananas. Mix well, but do not beat.
Pour batter into cake pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cake will crack slightly on top.
Don't worry.
Cool in pan.
It will remain moist for a long time.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and sugar. Mix well.
Add eggs, oil, and strawberries.
Pour into a greased bunt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Stir in pecans, chips and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls on foil cookie sheets.
Turn oven off when you place cookies in.
Do not open for at least 8 hours.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into tiny balls.
Place in a roasting pan.
(If you are making them ahead, you can freeze them at this point.)
Bake at 275°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Place a toothpick in each meatball to serve.
You can substitute pretzel sticks for toothpicks.
This is great at parties.

title: jiffy jello cream cheese treat
directions: Boil 2 cups of water and dissolve Jell-O into it.
Soften cream cheese in microwave and stir until smooth and creamy. Slowly add Jell-O to cream cheese mixture and continue stirring until well blended.
Add 2 cups of cold water; mix well and chill until firm.
Serve and enjoy.
It's delicious and has almost no carbs!

title: italian beef soup
directions: Thinly slice the steak.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic; remove and brown beef well.
Add the beef broth, tomatoes and seasonings and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add rice and cook 20 minutes.
Then add the cabbage and cook 15 more minutes.
Garnish with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add water, oats and butter or margarine together; let cool. Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, egg and egg whites.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix all together and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup dates or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine; add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add to mixture, as it begins to thicken.
Add salt and pepper to corn; add to thickened mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix beef, soup, sour cream, chilies and 1/2 cup cheese.
Line a 9 x 12-inch baking dish (ungreased) with chips.
Cover with meat mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Go answer the telephone.
Measure 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of salt and 3 tablespoons baking powder. Answer the door bell.
Let Carson and Wayne in to fix the ceiling fan in the living room.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: coney dogs
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown.
Drain; stir in sauce, beans, chili powder and sugar.
Bring to a boil, reduce to simmer and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Cook weiners as usual.
Place weiner in toasted bun and top with meat mixture.
Top with choice of cheese, onion and/or relish.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the crushed pretzels, melted butter and 1 cup sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish and bake 8 minutes in a 400° preheated oven.
Cool. Blend the softened cream cheese and 1 tablespoon sugar until smooth and fold in the cool whip.
Spread on top of the cooled crust.
Dissolve the strawberry jello in the boiling water.
Add the frozen strawberries
and stir until thawed.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Spoon over the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dredge chicken in salad dressing mix. Dip in mixture of margarine, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Arrange on baking pans and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Turn, sprinkle with paprika and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: zasu oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add red peppers, zucchini, onion and garlic; cook, stirring until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are very soft, about 20 minutes. Stir in parsley.

title: french fish
directions: Place fish in a shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread evenly over fish.
Marinate in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours, or overnight, turning fish occasionally (optional).
Bake fish, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Place under the broiler for 5 minutes to brown.
Serves 4.

title: baked eggs casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch round pan.
Hand beat eggs, milk, onion, oleo, salt and pepper until blended.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk and vanilla in saucepan. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add vanilla.

title: sugar-free egg custard
directions: Scald milk.
Beat together in medium bowl the eggs, juice and salt.
Stir in slowly the slightly cooled milk and vanilla.
Pour into 6 custard cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place cups in large baking pan with 1 inch hot water on bottom.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean. Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 3 strips of bacon.
Pour 8 ounces of tomato sauce over it. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crawfish or shrimp and crab meat fettucine
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add crawfish, shrimp or crab.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add jalapeno cheese until melted; add half and half. Combine with cooked noodles in casserole dish.
Top with grated American cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix melted butter with dry cake mix and 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Put half of cake mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes only.

title: easy cheezy scalloped potatoes and sausage
directions: Cook potatoes per package instructions.
Mix together.
Slice sausage and add to the potatoes.
Cook until sausage is warm, stirring often.
Add cheese stirring until well mixed.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding mixes with milk.
Mix with hand mixer according to directions on box.
Put this in fridge to chill.
Mix together in another bowl the cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Line bottom of clean flower pot with foil to cover the holes.
Mix pudding mix and cream cheese.
Mix together, then layer crushed Oreos and the cream mix.
If desired, put gummy worms in or on top of dessert.
You can also put a silk flower bush in the pot and serve with a clean trowel.

title: anchovy puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Add flour and chill.
Roll very thin.
Cut in rounds with small biscuit cutter.
Spread each round with anchovy paste and a few pieces of pecans.
Fold, making a puff.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 45.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese and margarine in small pieces.
Beat until well mixed.
Add sour cream and beat again.
Combine milk, eggs and onions.
Add to potato mixture along with salt, pepper and parsley.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Place in greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator at least 30 minutes before cooking.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until hot enough to serve.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mash potatoes while hot with milk.
Blend in eggs and set aside.
Lightly brown meat, onion and seasonings.
Add drained beans, soup and tomato sauce.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Drop mashed potatoes, topping in mounds over meat mixture.
Bake uncovered in preheated 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: nutmeg muffins
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking
powder and nutmeg in a separate bowl.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add flour alternately with milk to margarine mixture.
Beat well.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen nutmeg muffins.

title: orange breakfast flip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until smooth; serves 1.

title: chicken enchiladas(president bill clinton's favorite recipe)
directions: Preheat oil in a skillet.
Saute chopped chilies with minced garlic in oil.
Drain and break up tomatoes; reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
To chilies and garlic, add tomatoes, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano and reserved tomato liquid.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, about 30 minutes.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: bacon-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with a damp paper towel; remove and chop stems. In a skillet over medium heat, fry bacon until brown.
Remove bacon to paper towels and leave a small amount of grease in skillet.
Add onion and chopped stems and cook until tender.
Add crumbled bacon and the cream cheese to the mixture and stir to melt.
Stuff mushroom caps with the mixture and cover with some Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° on slightly greased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in 3 1/2 cups water.
Add cheese; beat in eggs, milk and garlic salt.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Should be firm when knife is inserted.) You may sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: easy microwave cheese sauce
directions: Microwave cheese and milk in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 4 to 6 minutes or until smooth, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve over potatoes or vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: orange bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, egg, orange juice and grated peel of orange.
Stir until mixture is dampened, but not smooth.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased casserole. Cover with soup and 1 can water. Top with cheese, cover with stuffing mix. Drizzle on butter. Bake 400° for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add 1 cup of flour, vanilla, soda and cream of tartar.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk on low speed.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, wafers and pudding mixture.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: judy's jambalaya
directions: Brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon olive oil in Dutch oven.
Add sausage and continue browning until completed (5 to 8 minutes). Remove meat from Dutch oven; drain excess fat.
Save small amount of fat to saute onions to golden, soft texture.
Add garlic and saute for 1 minute.
Return meat to pot and add all vegetables, Tabasco sauce and 3 cups liquid.
Simmer 15 minutes in covered pot.
Add 2 cups rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, until rice is cooked.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Stir dry ingredients alternately with milk into creamed mixture.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
(I use the tiny muffins and the recipe yields about 36.)
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger and eggplant casserole
directions: In a small casserole dish put a layer of potatoes, then eggplant, then hamburger.
Mix corn with eggs and flour.
Pour this over the 3 layers and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream cake roll
directions: Grease, flour and wax paper 3 cookie sheets.
Make angel food cake as directed on package.
Pour into pans and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
When cooked, remove cakes immediately from pan and turn out onto a clean dish towel that has been sprinkled lightly with confectioners sugar.
Peel off wax paper and roll cake in cloth, working quickly and gently.
Cool in cloth.

title: charlene's fried pies
directions: Combine ingredients to make dough.
Pinch off small ball and roll out in circle.

title: green pepper, tomatoes, cabbage and cheese(serves 4)
directions: Heat fat in heavy skillet.
Add onions; cook slowly 5 minutes. Place pepper on top; cook 5 minutes.
Add halved tomatoes, skin side down, and place quartered cabbage on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well. Chill 5 minutes.

Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass bowl. Top with 1/3 of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding. Chill and keep refrigerated until used. Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and pepper until mixed.
Add flour a little at a time until firm enough to make into balls.
Roll into small balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: casey's delicious honey rye bread
directions: Mix together milk, honey, salt and caraway seed; cool.
When at room temperature, add yeast.
Add rye flour and 1 cup wheat flour; beat thoroughly!
Add 2 1/2 cups wheat flour; mix to make a stiff dough.
Turn out of mixing bowl onto a lightly floured board or counter.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Form a ball and put into a greased plastic bowl (I use Pam spray).
Turn the ball around in the bowl evenly, allowing the coating to seal the bottom of the ball.
Then place the bottom of this ball of dough, now coated, facing up in bowl.
Cover bowl with a piece of plastic wrap.
Store in a warm place (85°) until doubled.
Takes about 45 minutes. Remove the dough from the bowl onto a lightly floured board or counter and divide into two equal pieces.
Do not punch the air out of the dough.
Shape into loaves and place in 2 greased (or Pam sprayed) 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Cover with plastic wrap.

title: tea syrup(instant tea)
directions: Boil tea in water for 2 minutes; strain and add sugar and lemon juice to tea water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
This makes a syrup which can be kept refrigerated up to 2 weeks.

title: overseas candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook over low heat until it forms medium ball not soft or hard when tested in cold water (not ice).
Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into deep pan until cool, then remove and put in wax paper.
The longer it stands the better it tastes.
Let stand at least 5 weeks before eating.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: aunt laura's zucchini pickles
directions: Soak zucchini in 2 gallons cold water and lime.
Drain and wash at least 6 to 7 times to remove all trace of lime.
This is important.
Let sit in cold water 3 hours, then drain.
Mix sugar, spices and 1 quart cider vinegar to zucchini.
This will be watery on top and not mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Simmer 30 minutes and seal in sterilized jars.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan.
Boil over medium heat for 1 minute.
Stir constantly; fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and let harden.
Work quickly, hardening doesn't take long.
Store in airtight container.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Add milk to the consistency of regular cornbread.
Bake 55 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put in bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add zucchini. Alternate dry ingredients with milk; add nuts.
Bake in greased tube or Bundt pan dusted with cocoa.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Combine buttermilk and baking soda in a 5 qt. saucepan, stirring until soda is dissolved; add sugar, butter, corn syrup, and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil; cook, stirring constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat, and let stand until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and pecans to candy; beat until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss. Drop by Tbsp. onto a lightly buttered baking sheet or waxed paper; let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer water with cinnamon stick and whole cloves 30 minutes. Strain.
Mix tea and juice together.
Add sugar and heat.
Makes 1 gallon.
Better to make a day ahead.

title: spinach bars
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat the eggs lightly and add them and the butter to the flour.
Add the onion and the thawed, drained spinach.
Shred the cheese, add it and mix well.
Spread in a well-greased 8 x 11-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until nicely browned and crusty.
Cut into small squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: happy home recipe
directions: Take love and loyalty, mix thoroughly with tenderness, kindness and forgiveness.
Add friendship and hope.
Sprinkle abundantly with laughter.
Bake with Florida sunshine on 350° sandy beach. Serve daily; give generous portions.

title: moist and minty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup mint morsels and vanilla, stirring until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer mixture to large mixer bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Stir in flour mixture.
Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes just until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut in 2 1/4-inch squares.

title: ginger drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, beating well.
Add molasses.
Dissolve soda in 1 cup hot water.
Add alternately with salt, ginger and flour to egg mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar icing.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter; mix well with flour, nuts and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Line a 10 x 12 x 2-inch pan with mixture.
Add 1/4 cup powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk; beat until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pretzel-cheese squares
directions: Cut the cheese into small cubes.
Insert a pretzel stick into each cheese cube and eat.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add pecans, vanilla and coconut.
Make into balls and chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
When balls are cold, put a toothpick in them and dip into chocolate mixture.
(Heat chocolate mixture constantly.)
Put balls on buttered pan.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until smooth.
Drain grated cucumber on paper towels to get rid of excess moisture.
Fold into cream mixture with wooden spoon.
Add 1 to 2 drops of food color of your choice.
Cut bread into desired shapes, using 2 to 3 inch cutter.
Spread bread with filling.
Top with bread.
Garnish with cucumber wedge.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and 1/2 of Chinese noodles. Put in casserole dish.
Spread the other 1/2 of Chinese noodles on top of casserole.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°or microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: crunchy spinach salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: green beans
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot; seal with foil. Cook until foil looks like it going to pop.

title: spiced tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in dish; cover with spices.
Combine oil and vinegar and pour over tomatoes.
Chill 1 hour (drain).
Garnish with parsley and dressing.

title: pizza bubble bread(makes 10 to 12 appetizers)
directions: Sprinkle a greased 12-inch pizza pan with the cornmeal. Separate biscuits and snip each into 4 pieces.
Place pieces in medium mixing bowl.
Add sauce and toss to coat.
Arrange dough pieces in an 8-inch circle in the pizza pan.
Sprinkle with oregano and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until golden.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan and make a cream sauce by adding flour. Stir and cook while gradually adding milk. When mixture thickens stir in cheese, red pepper sauce and salt. In buttered casserole, layer asparagus, sauce, and sliced eggs. Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 - 30 minutes, or until bubbling and hot.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter in chafing dish.
Add brown sugar and blend well. Add banana and saute.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour over banana liqueur and rum; ignite, basting banana with flaming liquid. Serve over ice cream when flame dies out.
Serves 1.

title: cheesy shrimp and grits casserole
directions: Bring broth and 1/2 tsp. salt to a boil in a large saucepan and stir in grits.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir together grits, 3/4 cup cheddar and all of Monterey Jack cheese.
Melt butter in a large skillet and add green peppers, onion and garlic and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir together onion mixture, grits mixture, shrimp and next three ingredients. Pour into a lightly greased 2 quart baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheddar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 -45 minutes.

title: granny evelyn's easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain all juice from dill pickles.
Slice dill pickles crosswise to form round slices, about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Layer slices back into dill pickle jar.
Add sugar layer, add layer of pickles, add layer of sugar. Repeat layering process until finished.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and canned milk for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Let stand 6 hours before cutting.
Makes about 4 pounds.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add cooked, drained spinach.
Remove from heat and mix in everything else.
Make balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
May be made ahead and reheated.
Double recipe for a party.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, eggs and bananas; beat well.
Add all other ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Beat well.
Stir in chips.
Bake in greased muffin tins in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: strawberry-rhubarb deep dish pie(people who don't like rhubarb may even like this!)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg; mix with fruit.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole; dot with butter and top with crust. Cut steam vents and sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown and filling is bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the sugar, vinegar, oil, onion, parsley, chives, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper in a plastic container; shake well and chill.
Pour over the spinach, bacon and eggs, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper, if desired.
Toss well and serve.

title: baked corn dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Combine all ingredients and melted butter; mix together well.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix together in a saucepan the sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and syrup gradually.
Boil gently, stirring often, until mixture reaches a soft ball stage.
Drop in butter and let cool before beating.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until mixture thickens and is hard to stir.
Pour into buttered dish. Cool before cutting into serving pieces.
Yields approximately 20 pieces of candy.

title: trout cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, margarine, onion, lemon peel, horseradish, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir in fish.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, or chilled.
Mix parsley and pecans on plate or wax paper. Shape mix into ball and sprinkle with parsley and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg and vinegar (or lemon juice); blend with milk.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Makes 2 crusts.
Bake at 425°.

title: yummy swirled peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs. Add milk and stir only until dough leaves the side of the bowl. Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead just until smooth. Roll dough out into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick. Drain any juice from peaches into the sugar water and sprinkle diced peaches evenly over the dough. Roll up the dough like a jelly roll. Slice dough into about 1/2-inch slices. Place in pan with the melted butter. Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls. (This looks like too much liquid, but the crust will absorb it.) Bake for 55 to 60 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: kentucky venison chili
directions: Coarsely grind venison and brown in heated oil in a heavy pan.
Add onion, garlic, and green peppers.
Cook about 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Add chili powder, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and salt.
Let mixture simmer about 1
1/2 hours. Add beans and allow chili to heat and additional few minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge beef in flour and brown in butter. Cook onions in butter until limp. Add seasonings and water. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until tender. Stir in soup and mushrooms and cook for 30 minutes. Stir in sour cream. Heat but do not boil. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: orange glow
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and eat.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in soup pot and heat until hot.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Beat in cocoa and food coloring.
Sift together flour and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Sprinkle soda over batter.
Pour vinegar and vanilla over batter and stir until blended.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8 to 9-inch cake
pans at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pineapple cranberry squares
directions: In a 9-inch square pan dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Fold in pecans.
Chill until firm.
In small bowl beat cream cheese with sour cream until smooth.
Spread over gelatin.
Keep chilled until serving time.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: orange pecan shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add sifted flour with soda and salt.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Spread marmalade on top.
Sprinkle on pecans. Top with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Arrange pecan halves on top. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly browned.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Drain, rinse, then crush in pot until chunky. Add salt and butter to taste. Add milk and pepper. Add more milk to cover potatoes, if needed. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: barbara's berry pie
directions: In large deep bowl, beat 3 of the egg whites and cream of tartar until fluffy.
Slowly add 3 tablespoons Fruit Sweet and beat until stiff.
Spoon meringue into 9-inch pie pan, spreading meringue evenly to form a crust.
Bake this crust 1 hour at 250°. Cool.

title: new method custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly.
When steam shows, remove from heat and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a silver knife comes out clean.
(This custard pie never gets watery or soaks crust.)

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Place flour and salt in bowl and make a well in the center into which pour milk.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat eggs lightly.
Stir into batter.
Add water and continue beating until mixture light and fluffy.
Permit to stand for 1 hour (optional).
Beat it again. Have ready hot oven-proof dish (about 10 x 10-inch) containing about 1/4 inch melted butter or hot beef drippings.
Pour in batter.
It should be about 5/8 inch high.	Bake the pudding in hot oven, 400°, for about 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 - 15 minutes longer.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix milk and Miracle Whip.
Then mix in flour and sugar.
Drop in greased muffin pan and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Add oil, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Beat at medium speed until mixed. Add nuts and apples.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 and grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt the butter and chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in sugar and allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended after each egg.
Stir in flour, vanilla and salt.
Add chopped nuts and stir until well blended.
Pour the mixture into prepared pan and bake 30 - 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In heavy pan, melt sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and cook about 2 minutes.
Take from heat and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop onto waxed paper by the spoonful.

title: apple-broccoli salad
directions: Toss all with salad dressing.
Start with small amount and add until covered to taste.
This salad can be made and tossed with dressing hours ahead of time.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken in small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil broth and cream of chicken soup, then combine flour, pepper, butter, milk and margarine.
Mix to form a batter; pour mixture over chicken and spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May add 2 chopped boiled eggs to batter.

title: hot cran-apple cider
directions: In large kettle, combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain.
Makes 25 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Rinse seeds and pat dry.
Spread on cookie sheet and let stand several hours to dry.

title: butterfly frosting
directions: Combine egg white, sugar and cream of tartar.
Add boiling water and immediately beat at high speed until thick and fluffy.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cream in a 4 cup measure.
Cook on High 4 minutes or until mixture boils.
Add chocolate and butter.
Stir to blend.
Cook 1 minute on High.
Add some of mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Stir egg mixture into remaining chocolate mixture. Cook on Medium 2 minutes.
Whisk in vanilla.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Reheat at Medium 30 seconds or more.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Cream cheese until smooth and soft. Add milk. Mix well until smooth and creamy. Stir in lemon juice.

title: tuna-rigatoni salad
directions: In large pot of boiling water, cook rigatoni 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and carrots; cook 4 to 5 minutes longer, until rigatoni and vegetables are tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water; place in large serving bowl.
Add tuna, bell pepper, mushrooms and tomatoes; toss to combine.
In small bowl, combine dressing, mustard and black pepper.
Pour half the dressing over ingredients in bowl; toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Toss with remaining dressing; mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: self rising flour
directions: Blend all ingredients and mix well. Store in tightly covered container.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add peppermint oil and food coloring.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar. Chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
Mints may be frozen in an airtight container up to 2 months.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: sin squares
directions: Mix cake mix with butter, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Press into a 9 x 17-inch pan for crust.

title: zucchini cornbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add cottage cheese and next ingredients.
Place in 2 baking pans, 8-inches square.
Bake in oven at 375° until done.

title: beef sausage
