directions: Combine all ingredients; shape in a roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill several hours.
Slice.
Fry or broil, or add to soups or casseroles.

title: caramel corn
directions: Remove any unpopped kernels from popped corn.
Place popped corn into a large roasting pan that is sprayed with vegetable oil.

title: fruit pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Mix milk, Cool Whip and pudding.
Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture. Take one 8-inch plastic flower pot and spray lightly with Pam. Put about 1-inch of crushed cookies on the bottom.
Then add cream cheese and pudding mixture.
Continue to layer and end with cookie mixture on top.
Place straws in the pot and freeze.
Put flowers in the straws and use as a centerpiece while cake is defrosting.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in a large mixer bowl; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from side of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake or top with brown sugar.

title: maple nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and granulated sugar in bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: marinated mushrooms 2
directions: Heat the oil in a small, deep casserole and saute the onion and garlic until onion is transparent.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, water, cloves, saffron, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes, adding more water, if necessary.
Add the mushrooms to the cooking liquid and simmer 5 minutes more.
Turn off heat, cover and let cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: texas barbecue potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out and reserve shells.
Mix potato with other ingredients except cheese.
Return to potato shells.
Top with cheese.
Place in conventional or microwave oven until hot and cheese is melted.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: At room temperature, combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients well. Pour in to an 8 x 8 inch dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 425°. Serve with Tostitios.

title: les oreilles de cochan("pigs ears" - cookies)
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add melted butter.
Add flour, sugar, salt and stir until well blended.
Pinch off a small ball of dough and roll out very thinly.
Roll into cone shape, pinching bottom together so that other end resembles a pig's ear.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Fry ears until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sift sugar over ears.
Cool, then enjoy!

title: banana raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine bananas, egg, milk, oil and cereal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir to break up cereal.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add cereal mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Use greased muffin tins or cupcake papers and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Mix all ingredients but applesauce and baking soda into sugar mixture. Dissolve baking soda in applesauce and stir until frothy. Blend mixture with rest of ingredients and stir by hand.
Place in a Bundt cake.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: walnut cake
directions: Make yellow cake as on the box; put maple flavoring and nuts in with liquid.
Bake at 350° as on box.
Ice cake; can put flavoring in icing.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce leaves or use as a sandwich filler or serve with crackers.

title: midnight breakfast(egg-n-cheese with potatoes)
directions: Fry potatoes in skillet.
While potatoes are cooking, mix in small bowl the eggs and a little milk; stir until blended.
When potatoes are done, drain off excess grease.
Pour eggs over the potatoes in the skillet.
Season to taste.
Stir until eggs are done or flip over like an omelet.
When eggs are done, add layer of cheese on top.
Cover with lid just until cheese has melted. Serve with favorite meat and bread.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut steak and ham in bite size pieces.
Salt and pepper; dip in flour and brown in cooking oil.
Add chopped celery, chopped onion, soy sauce and juice drained from bean sprouts.
Cook slowly and stir from time to time for about 1 hour.
Add bean sprouts; cook about 20 minutes.
Mix molasses with flour, using enough flour to make thick consistency.
Serve on rice.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: pesky beef and macaroni
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
While you cook the macaroni, heat oil in a heavy, deep skillet.
Dice green onions and saute in the oil for about 5 minutes.
Add the ground beef and sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Continue cooking until meat loses red color. Drain excess fat.
Add the stewed tomatoes and chili sauce and heat through.
Drain macaroni.

title: triple layer brownies
directions: Melt first 4 squares of chocolate and oleo; put aside. Combine eggs and sugar; add flour.
Add melted chocolate and oleo. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Combine powdered sugar, oleo and creme de menthe.
Spread on first layer and chill.
Melt the 2nd 4 squares of chocolate and 4 tablespoons oleo.
Spread on chilled layer.
Cut into squares before hardens. Mint flavor retained better if frozen.

title: icebox cookies no. 1
directions: Thoroughly
cream
shortening
and
sugars; add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well and shape in rolls 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper.
Chill
several hours or overnight.
Slice thin. Bake on greased
cookie
sheet
in
hot
oven
at 425° for 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in raisins, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell, bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: lasagne
directions: Prepare Plain Tomato Sauce.
In large skillet heat oil; add sirloin, salt and pepper.
Brown well and remove meat with a slotted spoon, draining
well.
Place meat in cooking sauce. Boil a large pot of water
with
salt
and
oil.
Cook noodles until "al dente", usually
about
to
minutes.
Combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, parsley,
oregano,
salt, pepper and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese; mix well.

title: wanda's cheese potatoes
directions: Bring potatoes and onions to a boil; let boil about 5 minutes. Do not overcook, as potatoes will become mushy.
Drain in colander.

title: fry daddy donuts
directions: Mix 1 part milk to 8 parts sugar.
Put holes in biscuits. Deep fat fry biscuits until brown.
Dip donuts in glaze.

title: venison meat loaf(deer)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato paste. Put in loaf pan. Top with tomato paste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Saute veggies and mix with all ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix well.
Press patties 5/8-inch thick.
Dredge in flour, then in beaten egg and then in cracker crumbs.
Brown in skillet and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients in a blender for 10 seconds.
Scrape sides and blend for 10 additional seconds.
Add 1 cup coconut. Blend for 5 seconds.
Pour into a buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes.

title: venetian cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 3 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Line pans with wax paper, allowing paper to hand over the short ends; spray paper.
Break up almond paste in large bowl.
Add butter, sugar, egg yolks and almond extract. Beat with mixer until fluffy, 5 minutes.
Beat in flour and salt. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into almond mixture until well blended.
Divide mixture into three equal parts.
Add green food coloring to one, red food coloring to another.
Leave last portion yellow.
Spread each part into a separate prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Immediately remove cakes from pans using waxed paper overhangs.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in milk overnight.
Cream butter, sugar and poppy seed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Begin with vanilla wafers and line bottom of dish.
Alternate with bananas, Cool Whip, wafers, etc., until you have reached the top of dish.
End with a layer of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
Ready to serve and eat.

title: bread dressing for chicken or turkey
directions: Cook giblets in water until tender.
When cool, chop them fine.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and add enough giblet water to moisten thoroughly.
This makes enough to stuff a 12 pound turkey or it may be cooked on top of the stove in a cast-iron skillet.
Stir continuously (add water or chicken broth as needed).
Dressing may get crispy on the bottom if you like.

title: spareribs
directions: Roll
ribs
in	flour, salt and pepper.
Fry spareribs. Add ginger and garlic.	Add sauce; cook for 1 hour.

title: my favorite chili
directions: You will need a large kettle.

title: monster cookies
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder; add to mixture. Add vanilla and cinnamon; mix well.
Fold in coconut (optional). Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 75 cookies.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put
in greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a
x 13-inch pan.

title: old fashion do-nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not roll too thin.
Cut with donut cutter and fry in deep fat.
Fry holes, too.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain the beans well.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put salad mixture in a low, flat dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add sugar and cream.
Add rest of ingredients all at once and mix thoroughly.
(Sometimes the pumpkin sticks to the beaters, scrape off and beat again.)
Pour into 3 greased regular bread pans (will make 4 in smaller foil pans for gifts).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, test with toothpick.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and flour. In a separate bowl, mix cheese and pineapple (be sure to drain pineapple first). Mix both bowls together and pour into a 1 1/2-quart dish. Crush Ritz crackers on top of mixture. Melt the butter and drip on top of the crackers. Cover and place in fridge overnight.

title: peggy's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package and put in casserole dish. Combine broccoli, onions and celery and cook until tender.
Drain and pour in with rice.
Combine Cheez Whiz, margarine, soup and water.
Cook until melted.
Pour over rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quickie soup
directions: Grill the chicken breasts and shred or dice. Put the chicken and all the other ingredients into a large pot and cook for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix
jello
and hot water.
Add everything but the sour cream. Chill
half
until real firm.
Then spread sour cream. Add the rest of jello mixture and chill.

title: blackberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan, stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside.
Place margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and place in 350° oven until margarine melts.
Set aside.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture becomes coarse.
Add milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board.
Roll dough into 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread berries over, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Cut dough in 12 slices.
Place in melted margarine.
Pour sugar syrup over slices.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: zesty clam dip
directions: Mix
all ingredients together, saving clams until last. Chill. Sprinkle
with
paprika
when
ready to serve.
Can be served with potato chips or crackers.

title: beef and rice
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients lightly and remove.
Stir-fry next 4 ingredients.
Add beef mixture and next 3 ingredients; mix.
At the end, add sliced green onion; remove from heat.

title: jalapeno hot cheese dip
directions: Mix together and heat.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces. Saute onions and celery in the margarine or butter. Add the soups, chilies and tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes. Add the chili powder, oregano and cumin. Simmer for 20 more minutes.

title: good carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour, salt, dry mustard and milk.
Add pepper and celery salt.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of carrots and cheese, ending with carrots.
Pour on sauce.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: mexican finger rolls
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
Grease an 11x7-inch baking pan.
Separate biscuits and pat each one to a 3 1/2 inch oval shape.
Place a strip of cheese on each.
Wrap the dough around the cheese strip.
Press all edges to seal.
Place the rolls into prepared pan, making 2 rows.
Combine the margarine and taco seasoning mix.
Brush over top of rolls.
Press the corn chips onto top of rolls.

Bake for 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm. Inside these crunchy rolls is a surprise tunnel of melted cheese. These can be reheated by wrapping them in aluminum foil and placing them in a 400 degree oven for about 8 minutes. They can also be made ahead, covered and refrigerated for up to 2 hours before baking. Makes 20 rolls.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Then stir in sour cream. Add extra milk if necessary.
Serve with remaining onions, cheese and bacon.
Yield:
10 cups.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet or cake pan.
Coat potato slices with butter on both sides.
Place directly on grill.
Brown on one side.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serve hot and crisp directly from grill.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 2/3 cup juice.
Chop peaches into small pieces; set aside.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in reserved syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir extract into whipped topping; gently fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into an oiled 6-cup mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold; garnish with additional peaches, if desired.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: apple angel pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and fold in egg whites.
Spread in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whip cream or ice cream if desired.

title: oven roasted vegetables with rigatoni
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine first 8 ingredients in a large roasting pan. Add olive oil and toss to coat well.
Bake until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes. Add broccoli.
Bake until crisp and tender (about 10 minutes).

title: 7 can soup
directions: Just mix all together (with juice in cans).
Heat thoroughly and serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: cream cheese party cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large mixing bowl until soft and creamy.

Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla. Spoon batter into paper-lined miniature muffin pans, filling two-thirds full. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add the beaten egg and molasses. Add the flour, baking soda and spices.
Mix well.
The dough will be a little sticky.
Shape the dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll the ball in granulated sugar and bake for 7 to 8 minutes (no longer) at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: golden beef quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spread crust with butter. Cook beef and onion until meat is browned. Spoon into pie crust. Whisk undiluted soup, eggs, milk, salt, pepper and thyme. Pour mixture into pie crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: dip for strawberries
directions: Combine cream cheese with marshmallow cream.
Add vanilla or other flavoring.
Add food coloring if desired.
Serve with fresh whole strawberries.

title: cowboy bread
directions: Mix self-rising flour and plain flour together.
Add shortening and hot water.
Make a dough.
Put in cookie sheet in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Don't forget to grease cookie sheet a little so dough won't stick.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in the unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until foamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix and add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured bread pans.

title: vinegar dressing(no calories)
directions: Combine all ingredients in measuring cup or cruet.
Chill. Use to marinate cooked vegetables or a mixed green salad.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add and pack the graham cracker crumbs.
Then layer the coconut, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, butterscotch chips and chopped walnuts.
Pour condensed milk on top and bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes until the top starts to brown.
Cut while warm.
Remove once cool.

title: southern chicken casserole
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
In Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon.
Add chicken and brown well on all sides.
Remove to a 2-quart casserole dish as pieces brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add all ingredients but flour, raisins and nuts.
Mix really well.
Now add flour, mix.
Add raisins and nuts now.
Pour into 2 bread pans; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried mushrooms parmesan
directions: Heat 2 or 3 inches of shortening in deep frying pan.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and garlic powder in medium bowl.
Stir in water, 2 tablespoons melted shortening and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Dip mushrooms in batter, drain off excess.
Fry in heated shortening, about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn as needed for even browning.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Salt lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Mash berries.
Mix with sugar and bring to boil over moderate heat.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Shut off heat and add Epsom salts.
Remove from heat; stir about 3 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal with melted wax.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Mix rice, beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup juice. Mix lightly.
Shape into 18 meat balls. Place in skillet.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cream potatoes as usual with milk, butter, salt and pepper. Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a large casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Cook sugar, milk, salt, chocolate and corn syrup over low heat; stir constantly until sugar dissolves.
Cover saucepan 2 to 3 minutes to dissolve sugar crystals on sides of pan.
Uncover and continue cooking to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat; add butter and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla extract and beat until spreading consistency.
If frosting becomes too stiff, add 2 or 3 drops of hot water.

title: rowser's famous melt-away teriyaki steaks
directions: Blend steak sauce and pineapple in blender until frothy.
Pour over steaks and refrigerate for a minimum of 8 hours.
Grill steaks on barbecue grill.

title: can't-wait-for-summer sangria
directions: Boil water, sugar and cinnamon for 5 minutes. Cool syrup and cover.
Cut up fruit with cooled syrup. Chill for several hours.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry frozen salad
directions: Mix all (or fold) together.
Spread in a Pyrex dish.
Cover and freeze.
Will keep for several weeks if kept frozen.

title: soft toll house scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by spoonful and space about 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
(Best results if using glass baking pan.)
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Use same size jars.
Mix well in pan over low heat until mixed and pour into buttered pan (big one).
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except frosting, and mix until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting when cake is cool.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Blend in molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with hot water.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: havremakroner(oatmeal macaroons)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg, cream and extract. Mix well.
(I use hand electric mixer and whip the first five ingredients until like whipped butter.)
Mix flour and baking powder together and add to the butter mixture.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Let batter rest 30 minutes.
Place by rounded teaspoonful on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for about 20 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cheddar swiss fondue
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook onion and garlic in hot margarine for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, wine and caraway seed.
Gradually add cheese, stirring until smooth after each addition.
Pour cheese mixture into fondue pot.
Serve with pumpernickel or French bread cubes for dipping.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In saucepan, steam broccoli until bright green and tender; drain. Arrange 1/2 of broccoli in 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with half of cheese and half of cracker crumbs. Repeat layers. Drizzle butter over top. Bake 30 minutes.

title: wilma's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Cool.
Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
To this add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with water/oats mixture.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan for 25 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl, mixing well.
Add to apples in large bowl, tossing lightly to combine.
Turn in pastry lined pie plate; dot with butter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425° or until apples are tender.

title: perfect scalloped oysters
directions: Use rolling pin and put crackers in a plastic bag.
Use approximately 1 1/2 packages of a 1 pound box of saltines.
Combine crumbs, margarine, salt and pepper and spread 1/3 of buttered crumbs in a greased round casserole dish.
Cover with half of the oysters.
Using another 1/3 of crumbs; spread a second layer; cover with remaining oysters.
Combine 1/2 cup milk, oyster liquid and 1/4 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce (dash of Tabasco if desired). Pour over oysters.
Top with last of buttered crumbs.
Garnish with parsley.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat on a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Spread undiluted mushroom soup over meat and sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top.
Wrap meat in foil, sealing with double foil.
Place seam side up in large baking pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender.
When roast is done, lift from foil and strain gravy.
Slice roast.
Place in serving dish.
Spoon gravy over meat.
Cover and keep warm in oven.
Dilute gravy if too thick.
Serve gravy with rice or noodles.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Combine carrots, onion and pepper.
Set aside.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil, mustard and sugar.
Stir well.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: piscataquis county beef stew
directions: Braise 2-inch beef cubes in deep iron frypan in butter.
Add onion and turn down the heat a little.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Place ribs on rack in large shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° until done, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave potato salad
directions: Place bag of potatoes on paper towel in microwave.
Make 1-inch slit in one side of bag.
Microwave on High 13 to 15 minutes, turning over bag and redistributing contents halfway through cooking.
Set aside to cool.
Break eggs into 2 custard cups and pierce yolks well with fork.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at 50% power for 3 to 4 minutes, rotating cups halfway through cooking.
Allow to cool and chop.
Mix potatoes and eggs with all other ingredients.

title: ruth's chocolate pound cake with cream cheese filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Blend in vanilla and add chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.

title: french lemon bars
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute oil, onions, scallions, green pepper, celery, thyme, cayenne pepper, bay leaves and garlic in a saucepan until celery is tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, and lemon.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp is pink.
Serve over rice.

title: romantic salad
directions: Combine Jell-O (do not add water) and pineapple in saucepan. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese; stir until relatively smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mold and chill overnight.

title: english muffin appetizers
directions: Split muffins; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended; spread on muffins.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
May freeze before baking; bake at 375° if frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (batter will be very stiff) and pour into 9 x 14-inch pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 340°. Remove from oven and poke holes over entire cake.
Pour glaze over cake and smooth so it goes into the holes.
(This is done on hot cake.)

title: pumpkin puddin' cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pour into 15 x 9-inch pan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Mix together the butter, mustard and sauce.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Dip in butter mixture, then in bread crumbs mixture.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple cake american
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Slice 6 apples and spread in the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl and pour over apples. Bake 60 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese sticks(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cheese, salt, pepper and flour. Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Sprinkle with milk and toss with fork.

title: crisco icing
directions: Alternate beating ingredients with flavorings at end to creamy consistency.
Excellent for Christmas cookies.

title: hunter's pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mix in pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: frankfurters in a loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Split franks lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
Fill each with a strip of cheese, relish or catsup.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Spread in pan.
Arrange franks crosswise on dough in pan, curving slightly and pressing to fit pan.
Press into dough slightly.
Bake until bread is light brown, about 20 minutes.
To serve, cut bread between frankfurters.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, butter and milk.
Boil 6 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients in large bowl. Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is all melted.
Pour into a pan (do not butter pan) and let stand a few hours before cutting. Store in tin box.

title: zucchini salad
directions: In a colander, sprinkle zucchini with salt and allow to stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze as much moisture as possible from zucchini. Combine remaining ingredients in ceramic bowl.
Stir in zucchini. Chill at least one hour.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 3 g, fat 8 g, calories 136.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add milk, oil, salt and sugar. Stir until sugar and salt is dissolved.
Pour flour into large bowl; pour liquid into flour and work until dough becomes stiff. Knead by hand for 5 minutes.
Put dough into greased bowl; grease top of dough.
Cover with towel and let rise until double in size. Remove from bowl and punch down.
Divide into 4 pieces and shape into long loaves.
Brush with egg white and 1 tablespoon water. Let rise again for 35 to 40 minutes.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: punch
directions: Combine above ingredients until well mixed.
When ready to serve, mix well with your favorite mix, sour or 7 up.

title: no cholesterol honey bran muffins
directions: Spray 12 large muffin cups with cooking spray.
In large bowl, stir flour, bran cereal, baking powder, salt and raisins.
In small bowl, stir egg whites, milk, corn oil and honey until well blended. Add to flour mixture, stirring until moistened.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients except pie shell.
Mound filling into unbaked pie shell; smooth surface with a spatula. Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and continue baking for 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.
Maybe even with whipped cream.

title: upside-down onion corn bread
directions: In skillet, saute onion rings in butter until soft, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Spoon into bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Prepare corn bread mix according to package directions.
Pour batter over onions and spread evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Turn out onto serving plate. Cut into squares. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: molasses doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add molasses,
sugar
and butter.
Sift dry ingredients and alternate with the milk.
Add flour, enough to make a soft dough that
handles
easily.
Roll
out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter and fry in fat at 350° to 375°.

title: charlie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Saute together butter and flour.
Add milk to make a sauce.
Melt the cheese into the sauce.
Combine with macaroni.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven or until bubbly.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in large pan of boiling, salted water.
Bring spaghetti to boil again for 5 minutes; stir.
Cover tightly and let spaghetti stand 20 minutes.
Drain in colander or large strainer.
Rinse with hot water.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Pull bite size pieces of angel food cake apart and put into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Fold in egg yolks.
Add beaten egg whites with sugar.
Fold in 1 pint of cream that has been whipped.
Pour mixture over angel food cake.
Chill. Keep refrigerated.

title: caramel custard (flan)
directions: Make a hot water bath to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Heat water as you preheat the oven to 350°.
In a small frying pan over moderate heat, melt the 1/3 cup sugar.
Shake the pan instead of stirring contents.
Once melted, the sugar will caramelize quickly.
As soon as this happens, pour at once into a 9-inch pie pan.
Tilt pan quickly to let the syrup flow over bottom and slightly up sides of pan.
Use hot pads to protect hands from heat.
If syrup hardens before you finish, set pan on moderate heat until syrup softens, then continue.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, water, corn syrup and salt until it forms a hard ball in cool water.
Then proceed to pour slowly over the whipped egg whites while beating constantly.
Beat until candy begins to harden.
Mix in pecans and vanilla; drop on waxed paper.

title: chicken diven
directions: Line bottom of greased pan with cut up chicken.
In large pan, heat Cream of Chicken soup, Pet Milk, oleo and chicken broth.
In a large bowl mix packages of stuffing together.
Then pour soup mixture over stuffing and mix together.
Spoon over chicken in pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
(Great dish for church dinner because it is a BIG one.)

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Work in softened margarine.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, anise and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and flatten slightly.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Slice butter into chunks.
Mix sugar and milk together into pan and bring to a boil for exactly 5 minutes.
Add the hot mixture to the other ingredients and mix.
Put in a glass buttered dish (fits into an 8 x 10-inch plus an 8 x 8-inch).
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in greased baking dish.
Place cheese slice over each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken. Melt oleo and mix with dressing; cover the chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: grandma's chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, bring water to a boil.
Add chicken, onions, green pepper, salt, thyme and bay leaf.
Lower temperature slightly if boiling too rapidly.
After 20 minutes, add potato, carrots and celery.
Cook, partly covered, until chicken and vegetables are cooked.
Strain the broth.
In the broth, cook pasta.
Cut up vegetables and chicken, if desired, and add to pasta and broth.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix with mayonnaise to make a smooth salad.

title: new potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix salt, pepper and garlic with olive oil.
Cut potatoes
into 1/4 slices or 1/8 slices.
Coat 10-inch glass Pyrex dish
with oil or Pam spray.
Add potatoes and mixture, pasting each
potato
as placed in dish.
Garnish with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Mix 2 cans mushroom soup, 2 cans chicken soup, 4 cans water. Mix and bring to slow boil.
Flour biscuits, roll it out, make circles.
Mix chicken, peppers and onions in center of biscuits fold it over, crimp it.
Drop into simmering soup, don't stir, let slow simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: almond filled christmas cookies
directions: Mix the butter, whipping cream and flour together.
Chill, then roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with small, 1 1/2-inch round cookie cutter (size of shot glass).
Sprinkle with sugar; prick several times with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Don't let them brown.

title: hearty rice casserole
directions: Combine all together and mix well.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: spiced cider
directions: Put together in percolator.
Perk until done.

title: beef roulades
directions: Cut steak into 12 long pieces.
Pound with hammer or heavy saucer.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Place 1/2 cup on each piece of meat.
Roll up; fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in large skillet in shortening.
Pour off any fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Stir occasionally.
Uncover, cook until gravy is desired consistency.
Serves 12.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain well. Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs, to soup and sour cream mixture.
Spoon into casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian pepperoni spaghetti
directions: Chop sausage fine and heat 5 minutes in a large skillet.
Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, onion flakes and salt.
Simmer in skillet for 20 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Add seasoning and mushrooms and stir well.
Cook for another 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle each plate of meat sauce and spaghetti with grated Parmesan cheese.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pine bark
directions: Line foil-lined 9 x 13-inch baking dish with crackers.
Melt brown sugar and butter in a saucepan, stirring to blend well. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. With an electric mixer, beat cream cheese, sugar, milk and 2 eggs until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.
Mix pumpkin, egg yolks, sugar, spices and salt in a saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add gelatin which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Cool mixture.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mixture and pour over cheese mixture.
Chill.
Spread whipped topping on top of pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts or crumbs, if desired.

title: meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, oatmeal, salt and pepper.
Shape into meatballs and brown.
Mix ketchup, water, sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed.
Let layers cool.

title: graham cracker coconut cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; cream together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and graham cracker crumbs alternately.
Add vanilla, baking powder, coconut and pecans.
Put in 3 greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° until done (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).

title: chicken with italian sausage
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of the olive oil until soft.
Remove and set aside.
In the same skillet, saute the sausage in the remaining oil until they are browned.
Remove and when cool, cut into 2-inch lengths.
Dry the chicken and season with salt and pepper.
Saute chicken in the same pan until brown. Remove chicken and pour off all but 1 tablespoon oil.
Add onions, garlic, sausage, tomato paste and wine and scrape up all the brown bits from the bottom of the pan.
Return chicken pieces to pan, turning to coat them with the sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Serve over lightly buttered noodles.
Serves 2.

title: lo mein salad
directions: Bring all liquid ingredients and garlic to a boil.
Toss with warm rinsed spaghetti.
Fold in sesame seed.
Chill 24 hours. Before serving, add scallions, lightly steamed broccoli, mushrooms and snow peas.
(You can lightly saute these in corn oil if you prefer.)
You can substitute or add ingredients such as carrots and asparagus.
You can turn this into a main dish by adding ground beef, pork, chicken or shrimp.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Place all ingredients in boiler and boil to 260° or until a small amount of mixture dropped in cold water becomes brittle. Pour into a buttered pan.
When cool enough to handle, pull until a light color and mixture hardens.
Cut with kitchen shears into bite size pieces.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions, beef and green pepper. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until brown and drain. Add rice, tomatoes and chili powder. Pour in casserole dish and place in 350° oven, covered. Cook about 1 hour.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar (adding sugar slowly) and beat until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time to mixture and beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg and add to creamed mixture together with buttermilk; mix well.
Divide into 8 equal portions; bake 2 to 3 portions at a time in greased 8 to 9-inch cake pans for 12 minutes at 325°. Stack cake layers while they are hot; let cool.
Stew apples, being careful not to get them too dry; remove from heat and add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mash apples thoroughly to the consistency of creamed potatoes.
Let cool before icing cake.

title: spicy grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Grill corn, covered with grill lid, over medium-high heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Turn often to cook evenly.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix and bake in unbaked pie crust at 350° until done.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons in 1 cup boiling water.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Cut sausage and place in 2-quart dish.
Add hot water.
Cover and cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in chutney and sour cream.
Reheat (before serving) on Medium for 2 minutes.
Serve in glass cooking dish or chafing dish with wooden picks.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Boil ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add 3 pouches Certo and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and skim.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice per directions.
Add other ingredients, reserving one cup of stuffing to sprinkle on the top.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
You may wish to layer, rather than combine ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
